00:29.370 --> 00:31.998
Was it all just a dream?

00:32.173 --> 00:35.336
God bless you, Florida! Thank you!

00:35.510 --> 00:39.241
Did the last four years
not really happen?

00:39.414 --> 00:43.407
Look, there's Ben Affleck.
He's often in my dreams.

00:43.585 --> 00:46.520
And the Taxi Driver guy.
He was there too.

00:46.688 --> 00:49.350
And little Stevie Wonder,
he seemed so happy...

00:49.524 --> 00:52.857
...like a miracle had taken place.

00:53.761 --> 00:55.956
Was it a dream?

00:56.130 --> 00:57.427
We want Gore!

00:57.599 --> 00:59.499
Or was it real?

01:01.569 --> 01:05.061
It was election night 2000, and things
seemed to be going as planned.

01:05.239 --> 01:07.833
In New York, Al Gore is
our projected winner.

01:08.009 --> 01:09.601
The Garden State is green for Gore.

01:09.777 --> 01:14.771
We project Mr. Gore the winner in
Delaware. This state has voted with...

01:14.949 --> 01:17.110
Excuse me, one second.
I'm sorry to interrupt.

01:17.285 --> 01:19.583
Mike, I wouldn't do this
if it weren't big.

01:19.754 --> 01:21.847
Florida goes for Al Gore.

01:22.023 --> 01:26.392
CNN announces that we call Florida
in the Al Gore column.

01:27.161 --> 01:30.562
Then something called the Fox News
Channel called the election...

01:30.732 --> 01:32.063
...in favor of the other guy.

01:32.233 --> 01:36.033
Fox News now projects George
W. Bush the winner in Florida...

01:36.204 --> 01:39.640
...and thus it appears the winner of the
presidency of the United States.

01:39.807 --> 01:41.866
All of a sudden, the other
networks said:

01:42.043 --> 01:44.876
"Hey, if Fox said it, it must be true."

01:45.046 --> 01:47.810
All of us at the networks made
a mistake...

01:47.982 --> 01:51.213
...and projected Florida
in the Al Gore column.

01:51.386 --> 01:52.853
It was our mistake.

01:53.021 --> 01:55.819
What most people don't know is
that the man in charge...

01:55.990 --> 01:58.390
...of the decision desk at Fox
that night...

01:58.559 --> 02:00.220
...the man who called it for Bush...

02:00.395 --> 02:03.887
...was none other than Bush's
first cousin John Ellis.

02:04.065 --> 02:07.159
How does someone like Bush get
away with something like this?

02:10.571 --> 02:14.268
Well, first, it helps if your brother is
the governor of the state in question.

02:14.442 --> 02:18.242
You know something? We are gonna
win Florida. Mark my words.

02:18.413 --> 02:19.937
You can write it down.

02:20.114 --> 02:22.275
Second, make sure
your campaign chairman...

02:22.450 --> 02:26.284
...is also the vote-count woman
and that her state hires a company...

02:27.855 --> 02:31.655
...to knock voters off the rolls
who aren't likely to vote for you.

02:31.826 --> 02:35.023
You can usually tell them
by the color of their skin.

02:35.196 --> 02:38.393
Then make sure your side fights
like it's life or death.

02:38.566 --> 02:39.931
This talk about legitimacy
is overblown.

02:42.904 --> 02:44.701
President Bush! President Bush!

02:48.743 --> 02:50.176
And hope the other side
sits by.

02:50.344 --> 02:52.778
And even if numerous independent
investigations...

02:52.947 --> 02:55.006
...prove that Gore got the
most votes...

02:55.183 --> 02:57.743
If there was a statewide recount,
Gore won the election.

02:59.454 --> 03:02.321
...it won't matter, as long as all
your daddy's friends...

03:02.490 --> 03:05.891
...on the Supreme Court vote
the right way.

03:06.060 --> 03:11.088
While I strongly disagree with
the court's decision, I accept it.

03:11.265 --> 03:13.699
What we need now is acceptance.

03:15.303 --> 03:17.737
We have a new president-elect.

03:18.806 --> 03:24.972
It turns out none of this was a dream.
It's what really happened.

03:26.547 --> 03:29.675
On the day the joint session of both
the House of Representatives...

03:29.851 --> 03:33.446
...and the Senate was to certify
the election results...

03:33.621 --> 03:36.385
...AI Gore, in his dual role
as outgoing vice president...

03:36.557 --> 03:38.149
...and president of the Senate...

03:39.827 --> 03:42.887
...presided over the event
that would officially anoint...

03:43.064 --> 03:45.624
...George W. Bush
as the new president.

03:45.800 --> 03:50.533
If any congressman wanted to raise
an objection, the rules insisted...

03:50.705 --> 03:55.506
...that he or she had to have the
signed support of just one senator.

03:56.110 --> 04:00.012
Mr. President, and I take great pride
in calling you that...

04:00.181 --> 04:03.014
...I must object because
of the overwhelming evidence...

04:03.184 --> 04:07.018
...of misconduct, deliberate fraud
and an attempt to suppress voter...

04:07.188 --> 04:11.750
The chair must remind members
that under Section 18 of Title 3...

04:11.926 --> 04:14.952
...United States Code, no debate
is allowed in the joint session.

04:15.129 --> 04:17.529
Thank you, Mr. President.
To answer your question...

04:17.697 --> 04:21.498
...the objection is in writing, signed
by a number of members...

04:21.668 --> 04:25.867
...of the House of Representatives,
but not by a member of the Senate.

04:26.040 --> 04:30.568
Mr. President, it is in writing and
signed by several House colleagues...

04:30.745 --> 04:35.512
...on behalf, and myself, of the 27,000
voters of Duval County...

04:35.683 --> 04:39.244
...in which 16,000 of them are
African-Americans...

04:39.420 --> 04:43.254
...that was disenfranchised
in this last election.

04:43.424 --> 04:45.756
Is the objection signed by a member
of the Senate?

04:45.927 --> 04:48.418
Not signed by a member
of the Senate.

04:48.596 --> 04:50.325
The Senate is missing.

04:50.498 --> 04:52.728
It is in writing and signed
by myself...

04:52.900 --> 04:55.391
...on behalf of many
of the diverse constituents...

04:55.570 --> 04:58.300
...especially those
in the 9th Congressional District...

04:58.472 --> 05:01.532
...and all American voters who
recognize that the Supreme Court...

05:01.709 --> 05:04.610
...not the people of the United States,
decided this election.

05:04.779 --> 05:07.270
Is the objection signed
by a senator?

05:07.448 --> 05:11.612
Unfortunately, Mr. President, it is
not signed by one single senator.

05:11.786 --> 05:15.517
I have no authority
over the United States Senate...

05:15.690 --> 05:17.282
...and no senator has signed.

05:17.458 --> 05:21.019
Mr. President, it is in writing and
signed by myself and several...

05:21.195 --> 05:26.132
...of my constituents from Florida.
A senator is needed, but missing.

05:26.300 --> 05:29.360
Is the objection in writing...

05:29.537 --> 05:32.904
...and signed by a member
of the House and a senator?

05:33.074 --> 05:35.304
The objection is in writing,
and I don't care...

05:35.476 --> 05:40.072
...that it is not signed by a member
of the Senate.

05:40.248 --> 05:43.149
The chair will advise that the rules
do care...

05:43.317 --> 05:48.653
...and the signature of a senator...

05:49.790 --> 05:54.693
Not a single senator came to the aid
of the African-Americans in Congress.

05:54.862 --> 05:59.663
One after another, they were told
to sit down and shut up.

05:59.834 --> 06:02.803
It's a sad day in America,
Mr. President, when we can't find...

06:02.970 --> 06:05.996
...a senator to sign the objections...

06:06.173 --> 06:09.199
- The gentleman will suspend...
- New Democratic senators won't sign.

06:09.377 --> 06:13.177
- I object.
- The gentleman will suspend.

06:15.283 --> 06:17.683
Inauguration coverage, 2001...

06:17.852 --> 06:21.344
...on a nasty, but it could be worse,
kind of day in Washington.

06:21.522 --> 06:23.217
- What do we want?
- Justice!

06:23.391 --> 06:24.756
- When do we want it?
- Now!

06:25.660 --> 06:28.527
On the day George W. Bush was
inaugurated...

06:28.696 --> 06:32.723
...tens of thousands of Americans
poured into the streets of D. C...

06:32.900 --> 06:36.199
...in one last attempt to reclaim
what had been taken from them.

06:40.308 --> 06:43.038
They pelted Bush's limo with eggs...

06:43.210 --> 06:44.905
Stay back! Get back!

06:45.079 --> 06:47.639
...and brought the inauguration
parade to a halt.

06:49.016 --> 06:52.213
The plan to have Bush get out
of the limo for the traditional walk...

06:52.386 --> 06:54.616
...to the White House
was scrapped.

06:54.789 --> 06:59.624
Bush's limo hit the gas to prevent
an even larger riot.

06:59.794 --> 07:04.493
No president had ever witnessed
such a thing on his inauguration day.

07:11.072 --> 07:17.238
And for the next eight months, it didn't
get any better for George W. Bush.

07:17.545 --> 07:21.743
He couldn't get his judges appointed,
he struggled to pass his legislation...

07:23.884 --> 07:26.751
...and he lost Republican control
of the Senate.

07:27.788 --> 07:31.315
His approval ratings in the polls
began to sink.

07:31.492 --> 07:34.928
He was already beginning to look
like a lame-duck president.

07:35.129 --> 07:39.589
With everything going wrong,
he did what any of us would do.

07:39.767 --> 07:42.258
He went on vacation.

07:55.116 --> 07:56.378
Oh, no!

07:56.550 --> 07:59.917
In his first eight months in office
before September 11 th...

08:00.087 --> 08:04.046
...George W. Bush was on vacation,
according to The Washington Post...

08:04.225 --> 08:06.022
...42 percent of the time.

08:06.193 --> 08:09.219
If I hit every shot good, people would
say I wasn't working.

08:09.397 --> 08:13.356
It was not surprising that Mr. Bush
needed some time off.

08:13.534 --> 08:16.094
Being president is a lot of work.

08:16.270 --> 08:19.671
What about these folks that say that
you're taking too long of a vacation?

08:21.242 --> 08:24.473
They don't understand the definition
of work, then.

08:25.479 --> 08:29.882
I'm getting a lot done. You don't
have to be in Washington to work.

08:30.051 --> 08:35.284
It's amazing what can happen
with telephones and faxes.

08:35.456 --> 08:37.447
Thank you so much.

08:37.625 --> 08:39.456
- Is this to Destiny and Bubba?
- Yeah.

08:39.626 --> 08:42.152
What are you doing the rest
of the day?

08:42.328 --> 08:45.264
Karen Hughes is coming over.
We're working on some things.

08:45.433 --> 08:50.700
And she'll be over here. We're working
on a few things, a few matters.

08:50.871 --> 08:55.934
I'm working on some initiatives.
We're... You'll see.

08:56.110 --> 08:58.943
There'll be some decisions
I will have made while I'm here.

08:59.113 --> 09:01.240
We'll be announcing them
as time goes on.

09:01.415 --> 09:05.442
The first time I met him, he had
some good advice for me.

09:05.619 --> 09:07.519
Governor Bush, it's Michael Moore.

09:07.688 --> 09:12.022
Behave yourself, will you?
Go find real work.

09:12.193 --> 09:15.458
And work was something he knew
a lot about.

09:15.629 --> 09:17.688
- Anybody want some grits?
- Yeah.

09:18.232 --> 09:22.259
Relaxing at Camp David.
Yachting off Kennebunkport.

09:22.436 --> 09:24.301
How you doing?

09:25.039 --> 09:28.031
Or being a cowboy on the ranch
in Texas.

09:28.209 --> 09:30.177
I love nature, getting
in the truck with my dogs.

09:31.812 --> 09:33.074
Oh, hi.

09:33.247 --> 09:36.045
George Bush spent the rest
of August at the ranch...

09:36.217 --> 09:38.378
...where life was less complicated.

09:38.552 --> 09:42.044
Armadillos love to dig the soil
looking for bugs.

09:42.223 --> 09:44.214
And...

09:44.658 --> 09:49.027
So I went out there the other day,
and there was Barney...

09:49.196 --> 09:53.656
...buried in this hole,
chasing an armadillo.

09:53.834 --> 09:55.802
It was a summer to remember.

09:56.637 --> 09:59.162
Afterward, he left Texas for
his second-favorite place.

10:01.876 --> 10:04.709
On September 10th, he joined
his brother in Florida...

10:04.879 --> 10:09.009
...where they looked at files
and met important Floridians.

10:09.683 --> 10:15.952
He went to sleep that night in a bed
made with fine French linens.

10:32.940 --> 10:34.703
Do you suppose he's pretty
confident...

10:34.875 --> 10:37.241
...on those numbers on Iraqi
security forces?

12:06.533 --> 12:09.331
Make me look young.

12:20.214 --> 12:23.047
Yeah, I've got a little,
sort of air noise.

12:23.217 --> 12:26.618
Yeah, just don't turn it up too much.
I don't want to blow my head off.

12:33.093 --> 12:35.118
I got a mike here
if they want to use it.

12:35.296 --> 12:38.356
Testing, one, two. This is
the Oval Office. Testing, one, two.

12:38.532 --> 12:41.990
Testing, one, two.
This is the Oval Office.

12:43.804 --> 12:46.864
Testing, one, two, three, four, five.

13:44.598 --> 13:47.123
We have something that has
happened here...

13:47.301 --> 13:50.236
...at the World Trade Center.
We noticed a flame...

13:50.404 --> 13:53.066
...and an awful lot of smoke...

14:00.781 --> 14:02.908
This is horrible.

14:13.694 --> 14:16.128
- Oh, my God!
- Oh, my God.

14:16.296 --> 14:18.560
Oh, my, dear.

14:21.468 --> 14:24.767
Let's go! Let's go, back!
Come on, let's go!

14:24.938 --> 14:27.498
Oh, my God!

14:29.476 --> 14:35.745
Save their souls, Lord.
Save their souls, Lord.

14:37.184 --> 14:40.984
Oh, they're jumping.

16:21.688 --> 16:24.316
On September 11 th, 2001,
nearly 3000 people...

16:26.260 --> 16:29.593
...including a colleague of mine,
Bill Weems...

16:29.763 --> 16:34.132
...were killed in the largest foreign
attack ever on American soil.

16:35.536 --> 16:38.733
The targets were the financial
and military headquarters...

16:38.906 --> 16:40.771
...of the United States.

16:40.941 --> 16:46.174
If anyone has any idea or they've seen
him or knows where he is, to call us.

16:46.346 --> 16:50.544
He's got two little babies.
Two little babies.

16:51.151 --> 16:54.052
As the attack took place,
Mr. Bush was on his way...

16:54.221 --> 16:57.054
...to an elementary school
in Florida.

16:57.224 --> 17:00.955
When informed of the first plane
hitting the World Trade Center...

17:01.128 --> 17:04.564
...where terrorists had struck
just eight years prior...

17:04.731 --> 17:08.565
...Mr. Bush decided to go ahead
with his photo opportunity.

17:08.734 --> 17:10.896
- Good morning, boys and girls.
- Good morning.

17:11.070 --> 17:12.834
Good morning.

17:13.773 --> 17:15.638
Read this word the fast way.
Get ready.

17:15.809 --> 17:17.401
- "Mad"!
- Yes. Get ready.

17:17.578 --> 17:21.069
- "Calf"!
- Yeah.

17:21.281 --> 17:24.478
Get ready to read the words on this
page without making a mistake.

17:24.651 --> 17:26.915
When the second plane hit
the tower...

17:27.087 --> 17:29.453
...his chief of staff entered
the classroom...

17:29.623 --> 17:34.788
...and told Mr. Bush,
"The nation is under attack."

17:37.497 --> 17:42.434
Not knowing what to do, with no one
telling him what to do...

17:42.603 --> 17:46.937
...and no Secret Service rushing
in to take him to safety...

17:47.107 --> 17:49.371
...Mr. Bush just sat there...

17:49.543 --> 17:54.845
...and continued to read
My Pet Goat with the children.

18:08.595 --> 18:11.792
Nearly seven minutes passed
with nobody doing anything.

18:17.504 --> 18:20.064
As Bush sat in that Florida
classroom...

18:20.240 --> 18:22.765
...was he wondering if maybe
he should have shown up...

18:22.943 --> 18:24.774
...to work more often?

18:24.945 --> 18:28.210
Should he have held at least one
meeting since taking office...

18:28.382 --> 18:33.342
...to discuss the threat of terrorism
with his head of counterterrorism?

18:35.922 --> 18:40.018
Maybe Bush wondered why he had
cut terrorism funding from the FBI.

18:40.193 --> 18:43.424
Or perhaps he just should have read
the security briefing...

18:43.597 --> 18:46.862
...that was given to him on
August 6th, 2001...

18:47.034 --> 18:49.059
...which said Osama bin Laden
was planning...

18:50.671 --> 18:53.606
...to attack America by hijacking
airplanes.

18:55.842 --> 18:59.369
Maybe he wasn't worried, because
the title of the report was too vague.

18:59.546 --> 19:02.037
I believe the title was
"Bin Laden Determined...

19:02.215 --> 19:04.183
...to Attack Inside the United States."

19:04.851 --> 19:08.446
A report like that might make
some men jump...

19:08.622 --> 19:13.184
...but, as in days past,
George W. just went fishing.

19:13.727 --> 19:19.495
As the minutes went by, George Bush
continued to sit in the classroom.

19:19.666 --> 19:25.127
Was he thinking, "I've been hanging
out with the wrong crowd.

19:27.140 --> 19:30.871
Which one of them screwed me?

19:31.611 --> 19:34.637
Was it the guy my daddy's friends
delivered a lot of weapons to?

19:36.650 --> 19:39.118
Was it that group of religious
fundamentalists...

19:39.286 --> 19:42.278
...who visited my state when
I was governor?

19:44.224 --> 19:47.887
Or was it the Saudis?

19:48.161 --> 19:53.326
Damn. It was them. I think
I better blame it on this guy."

20:00.073 --> 20:02.564
In the days following
September 11 th...

20:02.743 --> 20:05.906
...all commercial and private airline
traffic was grounded.

20:06.079 --> 20:11.312
The FAA has taken the action to close
all of the airports in the United States.

20:11.485 --> 20:14.613
Even grounding the president's
father, former President Bush...

20:14.788 --> 20:16.847
...on a flight forced to land
in Milwaukee.

20:17.023 --> 20:20.481
Thousands of travelers were stranded,
among them Ricky Martin...

20:20.660 --> 20:23.185
...due to appear at tonight's
Latin Grammy Awards.

20:23.363 --> 20:28.801
Not even Ricky Martin could fly.
But really, who wanted to fly?

20:28.969 --> 20:32.837
No one, except the bin Ladens.

20:39.913 --> 20:41.141
We had airplanes pick up...

20:44.551 --> 20:46.678
...Osama bin Laden's family
and other Saudis...

20:46.853 --> 20:48.514
...and transport them out
of the U.S.

20:48.855 --> 20:51.187
The White House approved planes...

20:51.358 --> 20:55.021
...to pick up the bin Ladens
and numerous other Saudis.

20:55.195 --> 20:59.894
At least six private jets and nearly
two dozen commercial planes...

21:00.066 --> 21:01.829
...carried the Saudis
and bin Ladens...

21:02.002 --> 21:05.438
...out of the U.S. after
September 13th.

21:05.605 --> 21:11.339
In all, 142 Saudis, including 24
members of the bin Laden family...

21:11.511 --> 21:14.309
...were allowed to leave
the country.

21:14.981 --> 21:18.041
Osama's always been portrayed
as the black sheep in the family...

21:18.218 --> 21:20.743
...that they cut off all relationship
with him in 1994.

21:23.723 --> 21:25.190
It's more complicated than that.

21:25.358 --> 21:27.758
Osama has had contact with
other family members?

21:27.928 --> 21:32.160
Right. In the summer of 2001, just
before 9l11, one of Osama's sons...

21:32.332 --> 21:35.199
...got married in Afghanistan,
and several family members...

21:35.368 --> 21:37.268
...showed up at the wedding.
- Bin Ladens?

21:37.437 --> 21:41.897
That's right. So they're not cut off
completely. That's an exaggeration.

21:42.075 --> 21:44.270
We now welcome to
Larry King Live...

21:44.444 --> 21:48.346
...Prince Bandar, ambassador of the
Kingdom of Saudi Arabia to the U.S.

21:48.515 --> 21:52.474
You had about 24 members
of bin Laden's family, and...

21:52.652 --> 21:55.450
- Here?
- In America. Students and...

21:55.622 --> 22:00.059
His Majesty felt it's not fair for those
innocent people to be subjected...

22:00.227 --> 22:04.186
...to any harm. On the other hand,
we understood the high emotions...

22:04.364 --> 22:07.925
...so, with coordination with the FBI,
we got them out.

22:08.101 --> 22:11.195
This is retired FBI agent
Jack Cloonan.

22:11.371 --> 22:15.808
Before 9/11, he was a senior agent
on the joint FBl-CIA...

22:15.976 --> 22:17.307
...al Qaeda task force.

22:17.477 --> 22:22.540
I, as an investigator, would not
want these people to have left.

22:22.716 --> 22:26.812
I think, in the case of the bin Laden
family, it would have been prudent...

22:26.987 --> 22:30.445
...to hand the subpoenas out, have
them come in, get on-the-record.

22:30.624 --> 22:31.921
You know, get on-the-record.

22:32.092 --> 22:33.889
- That's the proper procedure?
- Yeah.

22:34.160 --> 22:36.685
How many people were pulled off
airlines after that...

22:36.863 --> 22:39.423
...coming into the country
who were Middle Eastern...

22:39.599 --> 22:41.624
...or they fit a very general picture.

22:41.801 --> 22:45.897
We held hundreds of people
for weeks and months at a time.

22:46.072 --> 22:49.132
Did the authorities do anything when
the bin Ladens tried to leave?

22:49.309 --> 22:51.903
No. They were identified
at the airport.

22:52.078 --> 22:55.878
They looked at their passports,
and they were identified.

22:56.049 --> 22:58.279
That would happen to us
if we left the country.

22:58.451 --> 23:00.419
- Exactly.
- Interview, check the passport.

23:00.587 --> 23:02.145
- What else?
- Nothing.

23:04.190 --> 23:06.317
I don't know about you,
but usually...

23:06.493 --> 23:09.326
...when the police can't find
a murderer...

23:09.596 --> 23:12.463
...don't they usually wanna talk
to the family members...

23:12.632 --> 23:15.795
...to find out where they think
he might be?

23:15.969 --> 23:17.664
You don't know
where your husband is?

23:17.938 --> 23:19.496
If you hear anything,
let us know.

23:19.806 --> 23:21.671
Can you come downtown,
give a statement?

23:21.841 --> 23:23.240
- How long?
- You've got time.

23:23.410 --> 23:25.002
Mine's worth money. Yours isn't.

23:25.178 --> 23:26.907
- Send a bill.
- I asked you a question.

23:27.080 --> 23:29.548
- Answer them. Don't ask them.
- I pay your salary, cop.

23:29.716 --> 23:31.047
Sit down. I'm gonna earn it.

23:31.217 --> 23:34.778
Yeah. That's how cops do it.
What was going on here?

23:34.955 --> 23:36.422
We need to know more about that.

23:38.024 --> 23:40.151
It needs to be the subject
of an investigation.

23:40.327 --> 23:43.728
What happened? How did it happen?
Why? Who authorized it?

23:44.197 --> 23:46.358
lmagine what those poor bastards
were feeling...

23:49.402 --> 23:51.700
...when jumping off that
building to their death.

23:51.871 --> 23:55.534
Those young guys and cops
and firemen...

23:55.709 --> 23:58.405
...that ran into that building,
never asked a question.

23:58.578 --> 24:02.173
And they're dead.
And families' lives are ruined.

24:02.349 --> 24:05.477
- And they'll never have peace.
- That's right.

24:05.652 --> 24:09.247
And if I had to inconvenience...

24:09.756 --> 24:13.886
...a member of the bin Laden family
with a subpoena or a grand jury...

24:14.060 --> 24:16.494
...do you think I'd lose sleep over it?
Not a minute.

24:16.663 --> 24:20.360
No one would question it.
Not even the biggest civil libertarian.

24:20.533 --> 24:22.660
- No, no. It's just...
- No one would question it.

24:22.836 --> 24:25.634
You know, you got a lawyer? Fine.
Counsel? Fine.

24:25.805 --> 24:29.571
Mr. bin Laden, this is why I'm asking.
It isn't because I think you're anything.

24:29.743 --> 24:32.678
I just want to ask you the questions
that I would anybody.

24:32.846 --> 24:35.406
- Right.
- And that's all.

24:35.682 --> 24:37.946
None of this made any sense.

24:38.952 --> 24:43.048
Can you imagine in the days after
the Oklahoma City terrorist bombing...

24:43.223 --> 24:45.453
...President Clinton helping to arrange
a trip...

24:45.625 --> 24:48.423
...out of the country
for the Mc Veigh family?

24:48.595 --> 24:50.460
What would have happened
to Clinton...

24:50.630 --> 24:54.191
...if that had been revealed?
- Burn him! Burn him!

24:54.367 --> 24:56.733
Prince Bandar, do you know
the bin Laden family?

24:56.903 --> 24:58.700
- I do, very well.
- What are they like?

24:58.872 --> 25:02.706
They're really lovely human beings.
He is the only one I never...

25:02.876 --> 25:05.242
I don't know him well,
but I met him only once.

25:05.412 --> 25:07.607
What was the circumstance
under which you met?

25:07.781 --> 25:10.545
This is ironic. In the mid-'80s...

25:10.717 --> 25:12.878
...if you remember,
we and the United States...

25:13.053 --> 25:15.044
...were supporting the mujahideen...

25:15.221 --> 25:18.952
...to liberate Afghanistan
from the Soviets.

25:19.125 --> 25:24.153
He came to thank me for my efforts
to bring the Americans, our friends...

25:24.330 --> 25:27.857
...to help us against the atheists,
the Communists. Isn't it ironic?

25:28.034 --> 25:32.266
He came to thank you for helping
bring America to help him.

25:32.572 --> 25:35.405
And now he may be responsible
for bombing America.

25:35.575 --> 25:38.567
- Absolutely.
- What did you make of him?

25:38.745 --> 25:40.610
- I was not impressed.
- Not impressed?

25:40.780 --> 25:44.580
No. I thought he was a simple
and very quiet guy.

25:46.386 --> 25:51.756
A simple and quiet guy, whose
family just happened to have...

25:51.925 --> 25:57.625
...a business relationship with
the family of George W. Bush.

25:58.031 --> 26:01.057
Is that what he was thinking about?

26:01.768 --> 26:07.104
Because if the public knew this,
it wouldn't look very good.

26:07.874 --> 26:11.173
Was he thinking, "You know...

26:11.344 --> 26:15.610
...I need a big, black marker"?

26:17.250 --> 26:21.516
In early 2004, in a speech during
the New Hampshire primary...

26:21.688 --> 26:24.282
...I called George W. Bush
a deserter...

26:24.457 --> 26:27.517
...from his time
in the Texas Air National Guard.

26:27.694 --> 26:31.892
In response, the White House
released his military records...

26:32.065 --> 26:34.761
...in the hopes of disproving
the charge.

26:34.934 --> 26:38.836
What Bush didn't know is
that I already had a copy...

26:39.005 --> 26:43.772
...of his military records, uncensored,
obtained in the year 2000.

26:43.943 --> 26:47.037
And there is one glaring difference
between the records released...

26:47.213 --> 26:52.412
...in 2000 and those he released
in 2004.

26:54.787 --> 26:58.018
A name had been blacked out.

26:58.191 --> 27:01.991
In 1972, two airmen were suspended
for failing to take...

27:02.162 --> 27:08.567
...their medical examination.
One was George W. Bush.

27:10.970 --> 27:14.098
And the other was James R. Bath.

27:16.209 --> 27:20.145
In 2000, the documents show
both names.

27:20.647 --> 27:27.052
But in 2004, Bush and the White
House had Bath's name blacked out.

27:28.188 --> 27:30.452
Why didn't Bush want the press
and the public...

27:30.623 --> 27:33.751
...to see Bath's name
on his military records?

27:33.927 --> 27:37.363
Perhaps he was worried that the
American people would find out...

27:37.530 --> 27:40.021
...that at one time, James R. Bath...

27:40.200 --> 27:44.398
...was the Texas money manager
for the bin Ladens.

27:45.104 --> 27:47.265
Bush and Bath had become
good friends...

27:47.440 --> 27:50.705
...when they both served in the
Texas Air National Guard.

27:50.877 --> 27:52.344
After they were discharged...

27:52.512 --> 27:55.072
...when Bush's dad was head
of the CIA...

27:55.248 --> 27:59.207
...Bath opened up his own aviation
business after selling a plane...

27:59.385 --> 28:02.752
...to a man by the name
of Salem bin Laden...

28:02.922 --> 28:06.289
...heir to the second-largest fortune
in Saudi Arabia...

28:06.459 --> 28:08.484
...the Saudi Binladin Group.

28:08.661 --> 28:12.654
W. at that time was just starting off
in the world as a businessman.

28:12.832 --> 28:15.699
Because he's a guy who's always
tried to emulate his father...

28:18.271 --> 28:21.832
...he went into the oil business.
He founded an oil company, Arbusto...

28:22.008 --> 28:25.842
...which was very good at drilling dry
holes that nothing came out of.

28:26.012 --> 28:29.504
But the question has always been,
"Where did this money come from?"

28:29.682 --> 28:33.812
Now, his dad was rich. His dad
could have done this for him...

28:33.987 --> 28:36.046
...but his dad didn't do this for him.

28:36.222 --> 28:40.318
There's no indication Daddy wrote a
check to start him off in his company.

28:41.194 --> 28:43.754
So where did George W. Bush
get his money?

28:43.930 --> 28:45.659
I'm George Bush.

28:45.832 --> 28:49.165
One person who did invest in him
was James R. Bath.

28:51.871 --> 28:55.671
Bush's good friend, James Bath,
was hired by the bin Laden family...

28:55.842 --> 28:59.835
...to manage their money in Texas
and invest in businesses.

29:03.916 --> 29:09.752
And James Bath himself, in turn,
invested in George W. Bush.

29:11.624 --> 29:14.354
Bush ran Arbusto into the ground...

29:14.527 --> 29:17.325
...as he did every other company
he was involved in...

29:17.497 --> 29:22.059
...until finally one of his companies
was bought by Harken Energy...

29:22.735 --> 29:25.363
...and they gave him a seat
on their board.

29:25.938 --> 29:29.999
A lot of us suspected through
the years that there has been...

29:30.176 --> 29:32.371
...Saudi oil money involved
in these companies:

29:32.545 --> 29:37.812
Harken, Spectrum 7, Arbusto
Drilling, all the Bush companies.

29:37.984 --> 29:40.976
Whenever they got in trouble,
there were these angel investors...

29:41.154 --> 29:43.088
...who flowed money into
the companies.

29:43.256 --> 29:47.659
The question is, why would Saudis,
who had all the oil in the world...

29:47.827 --> 29:52.594
...go around the globe to invest
in this lousy oil company?

29:52.765 --> 29:56.792
And the thing is, Harken had one
big thing going for it...

29:56.969 --> 30:00.427
...which is that George W. Bush
was on its board of directors...

30:00.606 --> 30:03.769
...at a time when his father was
president of the United States.

30:03.943 --> 30:06.969
When you're the president's son
and you've got unlimited access...

30:08.581 --> 30:11.243
...combined with some credentials
from a prior campaign...

30:11.417 --> 30:15.444
...in Washington, D.C., people tend
to respect that. Access is power.

30:15.621 --> 30:20.217
And I can find my dad and talk
to him any time of the day.

30:20.693 --> 30:23.753
Yes, it helps
to be the president's son...

30:23.930 --> 30:26.057
...especially when you're being
investigated...

30:26.232 --> 30:28.462
...by the Securities and Exchange
Commission.

30:28.634 --> 30:31.467
In 1990, when Mr. Bush was
a director of Harken Energy...

30:31.637 --> 30:33.798
...he received this memo
from company lawyers...

30:33.973 --> 30:36.407
...warning directors not to sell stock
if they had...

30:36.576 --> 30:38.806
...unfavorable information about
the company.

30:38.978 --> 30:43.210
One week later, he sold $848,000
worth of Harken stock.

30:43.383 --> 30:47.251
Two months later, Harken announced
losses of more than $23 million.

30:47.520 --> 30:49.886
The James Baker law partner
who helped Bush...

30:50.056 --> 30:52.081
...beat the rap from the SEC...

30:52.258 --> 30:54.920
...was a man by the name
of Robert Jordan...

30:55.094 --> 30:57.790
...who, when George W. became
president...

30:57.964 --> 31:02.230
...was appointed ambassador
to Saudi Arabia.

31:05.371 --> 31:09.705
After the Harken debacle, the friends
of Bush's dad got him a seat...

31:09.876 --> 31:14.210
...on another board, of a company
owned by the Carlyle Group.

31:14.380 --> 31:16.940
We looked at which companies gained
from September 11 th.

31:19.952 --> 31:23.319
We turned up this company, Carlyle
Group, a multinational conglomerate...

31:23.489 --> 31:26.287
...that invests in heavily
government-regulated industries...

31:26.459 --> 31:31.590
...like telecommunications, health care
and particularly, defense.

31:31.764 --> 31:34.699
Both George W. Bush
and George H.W. Bush...

31:34.867 --> 31:38.098
...worked for the Carlyle Group,
the same company that counted...

31:38.271 --> 31:41.001
...the bin Laden family among
its investors.

31:42.008 --> 31:45.136
The Carlyle Group was holding
its annual investor conference...

31:45.311 --> 31:47.108
...on the morning
of September 11 th...

31:47.280 --> 31:49.680
...in the Ritz-Carlton Hotel
in Washington D.C.

31:49.849 --> 31:54.513
At that meeting were
all of the Carlyle regulars...

31:54.687 --> 31:58.145
...James Baker, likely John Major,
definitely George H.W. Bush...

31:58.324 --> 32:00.884
...though he left the morning
of September 11 th.

32:01.060 --> 32:05.019
Shafiq bin Laden, who is
Osama bin Laden's half brother...

32:05.198 --> 32:10.659
...was in town to look after his family's
investments in the Carlyle Group.

32:10.837 --> 32:12.896
All of them together in one room,
watching...

32:13.072 --> 32:16.337
...as the planes hit the towers.

32:16.509 --> 32:18.534
In fact, the bin Laden family
was invested...

32:18.711 --> 32:22.442
...in one of their defense funds,
which ironically meant...

32:22.615 --> 32:28.576
...that as the U.S. increased defense
spending, the bin Laden family...

32:28.754 --> 32:31.985
...stood to gain from those investments
through the Carlyle Group.

32:32.158 --> 32:37.221
Our commander in chief,
President George W. Bush.

32:37.396 --> 32:39.591
With all the weapons companies
it owned...

32:39.765 --> 32:42.495
...the Carlyle Group was, in essence,
the 11 th largest...

32:42.668 --> 32:45.535
...defense contractor
in the United States.

32:45.705 --> 32:49.232
- Thanks a lot.
- It owned United Defense...

32:49.475 --> 32:52.808
...makers of the Bradley armored
fighting vehicle.

32:52.979 --> 32:56.574
September 11 th guaranteed that
United Defense...

32:56.749 --> 32:59.877
...was going to have
a very good year.

33:02.154 --> 33:04.486
Just six weeks after 9/11...

33:04.657 --> 33:07.592
...Carlyle filed to take
United Defense public...

33:07.760 --> 33:09.785
...and made a one-day profit
of $237 million.

33:14.567 --> 33:16.558
But sadly, with so much attention
focused...

33:16.736 --> 33:20.228
...on the bin Laden family being
important Carlyle investors...

33:20.473 --> 33:23.033
...the bin Ladens eventually
had to withdraw.

33:23.209 --> 33:26.144
Bush's dad, though, stayed on
as senior adviser...

33:26.312 --> 33:30.009
...to Carlyle's Asia board
for another two years.

33:30.182 --> 33:36.143
As unseemly as it seems
to know that George H.W. Bush...

33:36.322 --> 33:38.620
...was meeting
with the bin Laden family...

33:38.791 --> 33:45.219
...while Osama was a wanted terrorist,
well before September 11 th...

33:46.399 --> 33:49.926
...it's very discomforting
for Americans to know that.

33:50.102 --> 33:54.766
George H.W. Bush is a man who
has, obviously, incredible reach...

33:54.941 --> 33:56.431
...into the White House.

33:56.909 --> 34:01.972
He receives daily CIA briefings,
which is the right of any ex-president...

34:02.148 --> 34:06.448
...but very few ex-presidents
actually exercise that right. He does.

34:06.619 --> 34:11.112
And, I think, in a very real way they
are benefiting from the confusion...

34:11.290 --> 34:14.521
...that arises when George H.W. Bush
visits Saudi Arabia...

34:14.694 --> 34:18.494
...on behalf of Carlyle
and meets with the royal family...

34:18.664 --> 34:20.996
...and meets
with the bin Laden family.

34:21.167 --> 34:23.897
Is he representing the United States
of America?

34:24.070 --> 34:27.665
Or is he representing an investment
firm in the United States?

34:27.840 --> 34:29.705
Or is he representing both?

34:29.875 --> 34:33.275
This company is about money,
not conspiracies to run the world...

34:33.446 --> 34:37.815
...or engineer political maneuvering
and things like that.

34:37.984 --> 34:41.215
It's about making money,
and it's about making a lot of money.

34:41.387 --> 34:43.786
And they've done very well.

34:44.790 --> 34:47.088
I could get you on-the-record
on this question.

34:49.562 --> 34:52.588
In the White House view,
there is no ethical conflict...

34:52.764 --> 34:57.668
...in former President Bush and
former Secretary of State Jim Baker...

34:57.837 --> 35:00.863
...using their contacts
with world leaders to represent...

35:01.040 --> 35:06.000
...one of the most well-known military
arms dealers, the Carlyle Group?

35:06.178 --> 35:10.877
The president has full faith
that his family will conform...

35:11.050 --> 35:14.918
...with all proper ethics laws
and will act properly in their conduct.

35:15.087 --> 35:19.023
Okay, let's say one group of people,
like the American people...

35:19.191 --> 35:22.456
...pay you $400,000 a year
to be president of the United States.

35:24.196 --> 35:27.688
But then another group of people
invest in you, your friends...

35:27.867 --> 35:32.668
...and their related businesses,
$ 1.4 billion over a number of years.

35:32.838 --> 35:35.568
Who are you gonna like?
Who's your daddy?

35:36.142 --> 35:39.077
That's how much the Saudi royals
and their associates...

35:39.245 --> 35:45.013
...have given the Bush family, their
friends and their related businesses...

35:45.184 --> 35:46.879
...in the past three decades.

35:47.053 --> 35:49.487
Seems like a very nice reunion
with friends.

35:49.655 --> 35:52.249
Is it rude to suggest
that when the Bush family...

35:52.425 --> 35:55.189
...wakes up in the morning,
they might be thinking...

35:55.361 --> 36:00.389
...about what's best for the Saudis
instead of what's best for you or me?

36:00.900 --> 36:04.836
Because 1.4 billion just doesn't buy
a lot of flights out of the country.

36:05.004 --> 36:07.199
It buys a lot of love.

36:59.091 --> 37:01.423
Sooner or later,
this special relationship...

37:01.594 --> 37:04.461
...with a regime that Amnesty
International condemns...

37:04.630 --> 37:07.155
...as a widespread human-rights
violator...

37:07.333 --> 37:09.096
...would come back to haunt
the Bushes.

37:11.137 --> 37:13.105
Now, after 9/11, it was
an embarrassment.

37:13.272 --> 37:16.799
And they preferred that no one
ask any questions.

37:16.976 --> 37:19.240
Investigation should have begun
on September 12th.

37:21.113 --> 37:23.946
There's no reason it shouldn't have.
Three thousand were dead.

37:24.116 --> 37:26.641
It should've gotten started
immediately.

37:26.819 --> 37:29.219
First, Bush tried to stop Congress
from setting up...

37:30.923 --> 37:34.359
...its own 9/11 investigation.
- It's important for us...

37:35.161 --> 37:37.493
...to not reveal how
we collect information.

37:37.663 --> 37:40.791
That's what the enemy wants.
And we're fighting an enemy.

37:40.966 --> 37:43.901
When he couldn't stop Congress,
he then tried to stop...

37:44.069 --> 37:47.129
...an independent 9/11 commission
from being formed.

37:47.306 --> 37:49.570
The president's position was a break
from history.

37:49.742 --> 37:52.677
Independent investigations were
launched after Pearl Harbor...

37:52.845 --> 37:54.710
...and President Kennedy's
assassination.

37:54.880 --> 37:57.747
But when Congress did complete
its own investigation...

37:57.917 --> 38:01.080
...the Bush White House
censored 28 pages of the report.

38:01.253 --> 38:05.121
The president is being pressed
by all sides to declassify the report.

38:05.291 --> 38:08.226
U.S. officials tell NBC News
most of the secret sources...

38:08.394 --> 38:10.055
...involve Saudi Arabia.

38:10.229 --> 38:15.929
We've given extraordinary cooperation
with Chairmen Kean and Hamilton.

38:16.101 --> 38:18.092
We haven't gotten the materials
we needed...

38:19.805 --> 38:21.932
...and haven't gotten them
in a timely fashion.

38:22.107 --> 38:24.098
Will you testify
before the commission?

38:24.276 --> 38:28.610
This commission? You know, I don't...
Testify? I'd be glad to visit with them.

38:28.781 --> 38:32.342
What it will do is, the hole
that's in my heart...

38:32.518 --> 38:34.850
...and has been in my heart
since September 11 th...

38:36.856 --> 38:42.522
I lost my husband of 15 years.
I am now by myself.

38:44.063 --> 38:47.032
I need to know what happened
to him.

38:47.766 --> 38:53.261
I know what I got back
from the autopsy.

38:53.439 --> 38:58.001
That man was my life,
and I have no plan.

38:58.177 --> 39:01.078
I was taking a class,
and they asked me...

39:01.247 --> 39:03.681
...what was I gonna do in the next
five years.

39:03.849 --> 39:07.444
And if I'm not doing something
with this, I don't know what reason...

39:07.620 --> 39:11.249
...I have to live.
So it's very important.

39:12.057 --> 39:15.549
Very important. Okay.

39:16.195 --> 39:17.719
Okay.

39:19.131 --> 39:21.224
Ignored by the Bush administration...

39:21.400 --> 39:24.426
...more than 500 relatives
of 9/11 victims...

39:24.603 --> 39:27.868
...filed suit against Saudi royals
and others.

39:28.040 --> 39:30.474
The lawyers the Saudi
defense minister hired...

39:30.643 --> 39:32.611
...to fight the 9/11 families?

39:32.778 --> 39:38.216
The law firm of Bush family confidant,
James A. Baker.

39:38.384 --> 39:41.945
So right here in the center of three
important American landmarks...

39:42.121 --> 39:45.648
...the Watergate Hotel
and office building...

39:45.824 --> 39:48.190
...the Kennedy Center over there...

39:48.360 --> 39:52.854
...and the embassy of Saudi Arabia.

39:53.198 --> 39:54.460
Yeah.

39:54.633 --> 39:58.262
How much money do the Saudis
have invested in America, roughly?

39:58.437 --> 40:02.339
I've heard figures as high
as $860 billion.

40:02.508 --> 40:05.500
- Eight hundred and sixty billion?
- Billion.

40:05.678 --> 40:08.112
- That's a lot of money.
- A lot, yeah.

40:08.280 --> 40:12.876
And what percentage of our economy
does that represent?

40:13.052 --> 40:14.314
It seems like a lot.

40:14.486 --> 40:18.286
Well, in terms of investments
on Wall Street in American equities...

40:18.457 --> 40:22.120
...it's roughly 6 or 7 percent
of America.

40:22.294 --> 40:24.819
They own a fairly good slice
of America.

40:24.997 --> 40:28.057
Most of that money goes into
the great blue-chip companies.

40:28.233 --> 40:32.169
Citigroup, Citibank,
the largest stockholder is a Saudi.

40:32.338 --> 40:36.001
AOL-Time Warner has
big Saudi investors.

40:36.175 --> 40:39.303
So I read where, like, the Saudis have
a trillion dollars...

40:39.478 --> 40:42.470
...in our banks of their money.
What would happen...

40:42.648 --> 40:44.616
...if they pulled that trillion out?

40:44.783 --> 40:48.310
A trillion dollars? That would be
an enormous blow to the economy.

40:49.088 --> 40:51.318
Can I speak to you for a moment,
please, sir?

40:51.490 --> 40:53.924
- How are you doing?
- Good, how you doing?

40:54.093 --> 40:58.086
Steve Kimball with the Secret Service.
We're just ascertaining information.

40:58.263 --> 41:01.232
Are you doing a documentary
on the Saudi Arabian Embassy?

41:01.400 --> 41:05.427
No. I am doing a documentary,
and part of it is about Saudi Arabia.

41:05.604 --> 41:08.266
Even though we were nowhere near
the White House...

41:08.440 --> 41:12.171
...the Secret Service had shown up
to ask us what we were doing...

41:12.344 --> 41:14.744
...standing across the street
from the Saudi Embassy.

41:14.913 --> 41:17.575
- We're not here to cause any trouble.
- Okay.

41:18.217 --> 41:20.310
- You know. Is that...?
- No, that's fine.

41:20.486 --> 41:23.512
We just wanted to get
some information as far as...

41:23.689 --> 41:25.122
What's going on, yeah.

41:25.290 --> 41:28.487
I didn't realize the Secret Service
guards foreign embassies.

41:28.660 --> 41:31.652
- Not usually, no, sir.
- No. Do they give you any trouble?

41:31.830 --> 41:34.822
- Saudis?
- No comment on that.

41:35.000 --> 41:36.797
Okay, I'll take that as a yes.

41:36.969 --> 41:38.334
Good. Thank you very much.

41:38.504 --> 41:41.166
It turns out that Saudi Prince Bandar
is perhaps...

41:41.340 --> 41:43.604
...the best-protected ambassador
in the U.S.

41:43.776 --> 41:47.906
The U.S. State Department provides
him with a six-man security detail.

41:48.080 --> 41:51.015
Considering how he and his family
and the Saudi elite...

41:51.183 --> 41:56.280
...own 7 percent of America,
it's probably not a bad idea.

41:57.723 --> 41:59.953
Prince Bandar was so close
to the Bushes...

42:00.125 --> 42:02.525
...they considered him a member
of the family.

42:02.694 --> 42:05.993
They even had a nickname for him:
Bandar Bush.

42:06.165 --> 42:10.534
Two nights after September 11 th,
George Bush invited Bandar Bush...

42:10.702 --> 42:14.832
...over to the White House
for a private dinner and a talk.

42:15.007 --> 42:17.635
Even though bin Laden
was a Saudi...

42:17.810 --> 42:20.643
...and Saudi money
had funded al Qaeda...

42:20.813 --> 42:24.442
...and 15 of the 19 hijackers
were Saudis...

42:24.716 --> 42:28.447
...here was the Saudi ambassador,
casually dining with the president...

42:28.620 --> 42:31.020
...on September 13th.

42:31.690 --> 42:34.352
What were they talking about?

42:34.526 --> 42:38.656
Were they commiserating
or comparing notes?

42:39.798 --> 42:41.857
Why would Bandar's government...

42:42.334 --> 42:45.667
...block American investigators
from talking to the relatives...

42:45.838 --> 42:48.329
...of the 15 hijackers?

42:50.042 --> 42:52.272
Why would Saudi Arabia
become reluctant...

42:52.444 --> 42:54.674
...to freeze the hijackers' assets?

42:58.317 --> 43:00.979
The two of them walked out
on the Truman Balcony...

43:01.153 --> 43:04.645
...so that Bandar could smoke a cigar
and have a drink.

43:05.090 --> 43:10.858
In the distance, across the Potomac,
was the Pentagon, partially in ruins.

43:11.029 --> 43:15.159
I wonder if Mr. Bush
told Prince Bandar not to worry...

43:15.334 --> 43:19.031
...because he already had a plan
in motion.

43:20.005 --> 43:20.139
You come in September 12th...

43:20.139 --> 43:21.265
You come in September 12th...

43:23.108 --> 43:26.566
...to plot our response to al Qaeda.
Let me talk about the response...

43:26.745 --> 43:29.145
...you got from top administration
officials.

43:29.314 --> 43:31.748
On that day, what did the president
say to you?

43:31.917 --> 43:36.251
The president, in a very intimidating
way, left me and my staff...

43:36.421 --> 43:39.390
...with the clear indication
he wanted us to come back...

43:39.558 --> 43:42.584
...with the word that there was
an Iraqi hand behind 9l11.

43:42.761 --> 43:46.492
They planned to do something about
Iraq before they came into office.

43:46.665 --> 43:49.532
Did he ask about any other nations
other than Iraq?

43:49.701 --> 43:53.102
No, not at all. It was, "Iraq, Saddam,
find out, get back to me."

43:53.272 --> 43:55.866
Were his questions more about Iraq
than al Qaeda?

43:56.041 --> 43:58.305
Absolutely. He didn't ask me
about al Qaeda.

43:58.477 --> 44:01.446
And the reaction you got from
the defense secretary, Rumsfeld...

44:01.613 --> 44:04.013
...from his assistant, Paul Wolfowitz?

44:04.183 --> 44:06.651
Donald Rumsfeld said...
When we talked about bombing...

44:06.818 --> 44:09.013
...the al Qaeda infrastructure
in Afghanistan...

44:09.188 --> 44:11.713
...he said, "There are
no good targets in Afghanistan.

44:11.890 --> 44:13.118
Let's bomb Iraq."

44:13.292 --> 44:15.988
And we said, "But Iraq had nothing
to do with this."

44:16.161 --> 44:19.096
That didn't make much difference.
The reason they had...

44:19.264 --> 44:22.995
...to do Afghanistan first was, it was
obvious al Qaeda attacked us.

44:23.168 --> 44:26.069
And it was obvious that al Qaeda
was in Afghanistan.

44:26.238 --> 44:29.765
Americans wouldn't stand by
if we'd done nothing on Afghanistan.

44:46.258 --> 44:49.091
The United States began bombing
Afghanistan...

44:49.261 --> 44:52.822
...just four weeks after 9/11.
Mr. Bush said he was doing so...

44:52.998 --> 44:55.660
...because the Taliban government
of Afghanistan...

44:55.834 --> 44:58.325
...had been harboring bin Laden.

44:59.338 --> 45:01.067
We will smoke them
out of their holes.

45:01.240 --> 45:02.605
We're gonna smoke them out.

45:02.774 --> 45:06.801
- We'll smoke him out of his cave.
- Let's rush them and smoke them out.

45:06.979 --> 45:11.678
For all his tough talk,
Bush really didn't do much.

45:11.850 --> 45:14.842
Well, what they did was slow
and small.

45:15.020 --> 45:18.046
They put only 11,000 troops
into Afghanistan.

45:18.223 --> 45:20.282
There are more police here
in Manhattan.

45:20.459 --> 45:23.860
More in Manhattan than there are
U.S. troops in Afghanistan.

45:24.029 --> 45:27.988
The president botched the response.
He should have gone after bin Laden.

45:28.166 --> 45:31.897
The U.S. Special Forces didn't get into
the area where bin Laden was...

45:32.070 --> 45:35.665
...for two months.
- Two months?

45:35.841 --> 45:38.366
A mass murderer who attacked
the United States...

45:38.543 --> 45:41.034
...was given a two-month head start?

45:41.213 --> 45:43.875
Who in their right mind
would do that?

45:44.049 --> 45:46.779
- Dang! Anybody say "nice shot"?
- Nice shot.

45:46.952 --> 45:48.510
Hell of a shot.

45:48.687 --> 45:52.350
Or was the war in Afghanistan
really about something else?

45:52.524 --> 45:56.051
Perhaps the answer
was in Houston, Texas.

45:58.664 --> 46:02.498
In 1997, while George W. Bush
was governor of Texas...

46:02.668 --> 46:06.900
...a delegation of Taliban leaders
from Afghanistan flew to Houston...

46:07.072 --> 46:09.131
...to meet with Unocal executives...

46:09.308 --> 46:12.607
...to discuss the building of a pipeline
through Afghanistan...

46:12.778 --> 46:15.804
...bringing natural gas
from the Caspian Sea.

46:15.981 --> 46:18.472
And who got a Caspian Sea
drilling contract...

46:18.650 --> 46:21.483
...the same day Unocal
signed the pipeline deal?

46:21.653 --> 46:25.521
A company headed by a man
named Dick Cheney. Halliburton.

46:25.691 --> 46:27.852
From the point of view
of the U.S. government...

46:29.461 --> 46:31.258
...this was kind of a magic pipeline...

46:31.430 --> 46:33.762
...because it could serve
so many purposes.

46:33.932 --> 46:37.299
And who else stood to benefit
from the pipeline?

46:37.469 --> 46:40.768
Bush's number-one campaign
contributor, Kenneth Lay...

46:40.939 --> 46:43.407
...and the good people of Enron.

46:45.344 --> 46:47.574
Only the British press
covered this trip.

46:47.946 --> 46:51.575
Then in 2001, just five and a half
months before 9/11...

46:53.151 --> 46:55.619
...the Bush administration welcomed
a Taliban envoy...

46:55.787 --> 46:57.345
...to tour the United States...

46:57.522 --> 47:00.389
...to help improve the image
of the Taliban government.

47:00.559 --> 47:04.120
You have imprisoned the women.
It's a horror, let me tell you.

47:04.296 --> 47:07.595
I'm sorry to your husband. He must
have a difficult time with you.

47:07.766 --> 47:10.564
Here is the Taliban official
visiting our State Department...

47:12.137 --> 47:13.832
...to meet with U.S. officials.

47:14.639 --> 47:17.870
Why would the Bush administration
allow a Taliban leader...

47:18.043 --> 47:21.069
...to visit the United States,
knowing that the Taliban...

47:21.246 --> 47:24.545
...were harboring the man
who bombed the U.S.S. Cole...

47:24.716 --> 47:27.276
...and our African embassies?

47:27.452 --> 47:31.081
Well, I guess 9/11 put a stop to that.

47:31.256 --> 47:34.248
When the invasion of Afghanistan
was complete...

47:34.426 --> 47:37.759
...we installed its new president,
Hamid Karzai.

47:37.929 --> 47:40.295
Who was Hamid Karzai?

47:40.465 --> 47:43.901
He was a former adviser to Unocal.

47:44.069 --> 47:47.061
Bush also appointed,
as our envoy to Afghanistan...

47:47.239 --> 47:52.802
...Zalmay Khalilzad, who was also
a former Unocal adviser.

47:53.812 --> 47:57.578
I guess you can probably see
where this is leading.

47:57.749 --> 48:01.014
Faster than you can say, "Black gold,
Texas tea, " Afghanistan signed...

48:01.186 --> 48:03.586
...an agreement with her
neighboring countries...

48:03.755 --> 48:08.852
...to build a pipeline carrying
natural gas from the Caspian Sea.

48:09.361 --> 48:11.352
Oh, and the Taliban?

48:12.297 --> 48:14.788
Oh, they mostly got away.

48:15.333 --> 48:18.598
As did Osama bin Laden
and most of al Qaeda.

48:19.070 --> 48:21.698
Terror is bigger than one person.

48:21.873 --> 48:26.173
And he's a person who's now
been marginalized.

48:26.344 --> 48:27.834
So I don't know where he is.

48:28.013 --> 48:31.312
I just don't spend that much time
on him, to be honest with you.

48:31.483 --> 48:35.442
Didn't spend much time on him?
What kind of president was he?

48:35.754 --> 48:39.554
I'm a war president. I make decisions
here in the Oval Office...

48:39.724 --> 48:43.023
...in foreign policy matters
with war on my mind.

48:43.628 --> 48:47.120
With the war in Afghanistan over
and bin Laden forgotten...

48:47.299 --> 48:49.893
...the war president had
a new target:

48:52.103 --> 48:54.731
The American people.

48:58.009 --> 49:01.570
We've got an unusual terror warning
from the feds to tell you about.

49:01.746 --> 49:03.805
Fox News has obtained
an FBI bulletin...

49:03.982 --> 49:07.440
...that warns terrorists could use
pen guns, like in James Bond...

49:07.619 --> 49:09.644
...filled with poison.
- Good evening.

49:09.821 --> 49:13.382
America is on high alert tonight,
just four days before Christmas.

49:13.558 --> 49:17.995
- A possible terror threat.
- As bad as or worse than 9l11.

49:18.163 --> 49:21.758
But where? How?
There's nothing specific to report.

49:21.933 --> 49:25.869
Be on the lookout for model airplanes
packed with explosives.

49:27.572 --> 49:31.133
The FBI is warning ferries may be
considered particularly at risk...

49:31.309 --> 49:33.243
...for hijacking.

49:34.446 --> 49:37.643
Could these cattle be a target
for terrorists?

49:39.784 --> 49:41.308
- Fear works.
- Fear does work, yes.

49:44.289 --> 49:46.154
You can make people do anything
if they're afraid.

49:46.324 --> 49:48.087
And how do you make them afraid?

49:48.260 --> 49:53.926
Well, you make them afraid
by creating an aura of endless threat.

49:54.099 --> 49:55.691
They played us like an organ.

49:55.867 --> 50:00.736
They raised the orange, up to red,
then they dropped it back to orange.

50:00.906 --> 50:04.933
I mean, they gave these mixed
messages, which were crazy-making.

50:05.110 --> 50:08.477
The world is changed
after September the 11 th.

50:08.647 --> 50:10.979
It's changed because
we're no longer safe.

50:11.149 --> 50:15.381
Fly and enjoy America's
great destination spots.

50:15.554 --> 50:18.580
We have entered what may
prove to be the most dangerous...

50:18.757 --> 50:20.952
...security environment
the world's known.

50:21.126 --> 50:23.617
Take your families and enjoy life.

50:23.795 --> 50:26.025
Terrorists are doing everything
they can...

50:26.197 --> 50:28.495
...to gain even deadlier means
of striking us.

50:29.034 --> 50:32.868
- Go down to Disney World in Florida.
- It's like training a dog.

50:33.038 --> 50:36.872
You tell him sit down and roll over
at the same time, dog doesn't know...

50:37.042 --> 50:40.102
...what to do. American people
were being treated like that.

50:40.278 --> 50:45.181
It was very, very skillfully and ugly,
in what they did.

50:45.350 --> 50:47.784
We must stop the terror.

50:47.953 --> 50:54.358
I call upon all nations to do everything
they can to stop these terrorist killers.

50:55.093 --> 50:56.685
Thank you.

50:56.861 --> 50:58.089
Now watch this drive.

51:00.932 --> 51:02.797
All right. You give me another one.

51:03.101 --> 51:08.164
They will continue, in my view, as long
as this administration is in charge...

51:08.340 --> 51:12.572
...of every once in a while,
stimulating everybody to be afraid.

51:12.744 --> 51:14.177
Just in case you forgot.

51:14.346 --> 51:18.646
It's not gonna go down to green
or blue. It's never gonna get there.

51:18.817 --> 51:22.253
There clearly is no way
that anyone...

51:22.420 --> 51:25.719
...can live constantly on edge
like that.

51:25.890 --> 51:27.653
The reality facing
American families...

51:29.227 --> 51:31.320
...is they're not as safe
as they used to be.

51:31.496 --> 51:34.090
Drug dealers and users looking
for their next fix.

51:34.265 --> 51:37.291
Gangs who roam the streets
in search of their next victim.

51:37.469 --> 51:41.064
And the growing threat of terrorists
means the need for protection...

51:41.239 --> 51:44.470
...is ever greater.
And now that protection is here.

51:44.643 --> 51:49.012
Zytech Engineering, LLC has
developed and tested a safe room...

51:49.180 --> 51:52.149
...finally affordable to the average
American citizen.

51:52.317 --> 51:56.083
Protection formerly obtainable
only by the wealthy or powerful.

51:56.254 --> 51:59.815
Heck, you can be sitting in here,
drinking your finest Bordeaux...

51:59.991 --> 52:04.155
...and enjoying life, while chaos
is erupting outside.

52:04.529 --> 52:07.623
Every family in America
should prepare itself...

52:07.799 --> 52:09.562
...for a terrorist attack.

52:10.035 --> 52:13.562
Now to escaping from a skyscraper.
John Rivers is the CEO...

52:13.738 --> 52:18.038
...of the Executive Chute Corporation.
Good morning to you, John.

52:18.209 --> 52:21.269
- Good morning, Matt.
- Tell me about the product.

52:21.446 --> 52:25.542
It's an emergency escape chute.
It's an option of last resort.

52:25.717 --> 52:27.742
How high do you have to be
in the building...

52:27.919 --> 52:30.547
...for that chute to actually
take effect?

52:30.722 --> 52:33.520
You only have to be on the 10th floor
or above.

52:33.692 --> 52:35.717
They can put this on themselves?

52:35.894 --> 52:38.294
Right. They can put this on
themselves in as easy...

52:38.463 --> 52:41.591
...as about 30 seconds.
It's real easy to put on.

52:42.000 --> 52:43.331
- Here.
- Sorry.

52:43.501 --> 52:47.028
That's okay. Real easy to put on,
but...

52:48.206 --> 52:51.437
When you first get this chute,
you're gonna wanna put it on...

52:51.609 --> 52:55.375
...and try it on a few times yourself.
- Jaime's having trouble putting that on.

52:55.547 --> 52:59.950
Is this something that you honestly
think, in a moment of panic...

53:00.118 --> 53:03.417
...that someone can operate
properly?

53:03.588 --> 53:07.217
Oh, yeah. It is. This is actually...
Jamie's probably never...

53:07.392 --> 53:09.622
...put this thing on before in her life.

53:10.428 --> 53:13.090
It's okay. It's something that,
when you get it...

53:13.264 --> 53:15.664
...you're gonna wanna put it on
several times.

53:15.834 --> 53:19.497
Despite the raising of the terror alert
level, residents here continue...

53:19.671 --> 53:21.468
...with their Christmas errands.

53:21.639 --> 53:24.870
Frances and her family do some
last-minute holiday shopping...

53:25.043 --> 53:27.477
...knowing al Qaeda is planning
to attack.

53:27.645 --> 53:30.808
She says being in Saginaw doesn't
make her feel any safer...

53:30.982 --> 53:33.007
...than if she was in New York City.

53:33.184 --> 53:34.412
Midland is close by...

53:35.987 --> 53:38.012
...and I said,
"Detroit's not that far away."

53:38.189 --> 53:42.148
I said, "That could be something...
And Flint could be something... Be...

53:42.327 --> 53:45.262
...concerns for people around here."
- You never know...

53:45.430 --> 53:47.455
...where they're gonna hit.
Never know.

53:47.632 --> 53:50.760
But one potential target specifically
mentioned by the terrorists...

53:50.935 --> 53:55.269
...has security officials baffled.
It's tiny Tappahannock, Virginia...

53:55.440 --> 53:57.101
...population, 2016.

53:57.275 --> 54:00.403
Such an attack could generate
widespread fear...

54:00.578 --> 54:05.982
...that even here in rural, small-town
America, no one is entirely safe.

54:07.552 --> 54:09.986
On the news there was
an alert in Tappahannock.

54:10.355 --> 54:13.188
- What did the FBI tell you?
- Well, they contacted me by phone.

54:14.826 --> 54:17.624
Basically let me know about this,
were it Tappahannock.

54:17.796 --> 54:21.562
- That's how it started.
- In the so-called chatter they pick up...

54:21.733 --> 54:25.191
...they wasn't sure Tappahannock.
There's a Rappahannock County...

54:25.370 --> 54:28.271
...Rappahannock River.
- There is a Rappahannock...

54:28.439 --> 54:31.033
A place called Rappahannock.
They got it mixed up.

54:31.743 --> 54:34.211
This is Tappahannock,
not Rappahannock.

54:34.379 --> 54:37.507
- Is there any target around here?
- Not that we can think of.

54:37.682 --> 54:39.547
- It can happen anywhere.
- Wal-Mart.

54:39.717 --> 54:41.685
A big spaghetti supper in here.

54:41.853 --> 54:43.150
Wal-Mart, probably.

54:43.321 --> 54:45.721
Do you feel extra suspicious
of outsiders?

54:45.890 --> 54:47.949
Oh, everybody does that.

54:48.126 --> 54:50.026
That's just something that happens.

54:50.195 --> 54:53.653
When I look at certain people,
I wonder, "Oh, my goodness.

54:53.832 --> 54:55.993
Do you think they could be
a terrorist?"

54:56.167 --> 54:58.294
- Never know what's gonna happen.
- Right.

54:58.469 --> 54:59.936
It could happen right now.

55:00.872 --> 55:03.397
Never trust nobody you don't know.

55:04.209 --> 55:07.872
And even if you do know them,
you really can't trust them then.

55:08.246 --> 55:11.238
From Tappahannock
to Rappahannock...

55:11.416 --> 55:16.080
...to every town and village in
America, the people were afraid.

55:16.521 --> 55:19.012
And they turned to their leader
to protect them.

55:19.190 --> 55:22.455
But protect them from what?

55:47.852 --> 55:50.082
Meet John Ashcroft.

55:50.255 --> 55:54.692
In 2000, he was running for
re-election as senator for Missouri...

55:54.859 --> 55:59.023
...against a man who died
the month before the election.

55:59.197 --> 56:02.257
The voters preferred the dead guy.

56:02.433 --> 56:07.063
So George W. Bush made him
his attorney general.

56:07.238 --> 56:09.604
He was sworn in on a stack
of Bibles.

56:09.774 --> 56:11.901
Because when you can't beat
a dead guy...

56:12.076 --> 56:14.374
...you need all the help you can get.

56:14.545 --> 56:16.570
During the summer before 9/11...

56:16.748 --> 56:19.740
...Ashcroft told acting FBI director,
Thomas Pickard...

56:19.918 --> 56:23.615
...that he didn't want to hear
anything more about terrorist threats.

56:23.788 --> 56:28.054
Mr. Watson had come to you and said
that the CIA was very concerned...

56:28.226 --> 56:30.194
...that there would be an attack.

56:30.361 --> 56:34.764
You said that you told the attorney
general this fact repeatedly...

56:34.933 --> 56:36.924
...in these meetings. That correct?

56:37.101 --> 56:38.898
I've told him at least
on two occasions.

56:40.471 --> 56:43.133
And you told the staff,
according to this statement...

56:43.308 --> 56:47.972
...Mr. Ashcroft told you that he did not
want to hear about this anymore.

56:48.146 --> 56:50.842
- Is that correct?
- That is correct.

56:51.015 --> 56:54.416
His own FBI knew that summer
there were al Qaeda members...

56:54.585 --> 56:58.544
...in the U.S. and bin Laden was
sending his agents to flight schools...

56:58.723 --> 57:00.350
...around the country.

57:00.525 --> 57:04.052
But Ashcroft's Justice Department
turned a blind eye...

57:04.228 --> 57:05.695
...and a deaf ear.

57:05.863 --> 57:10.095
But after 9/11, John Ashcroft
had some brilliant ideas...

57:10.268 --> 57:12.202
...for how to protect America.

57:12.370 --> 57:15.032
The Patriot Act, adopted by Congress
and signed by Bush...

57:15.206 --> 57:16.901
...six weeks after the attacks...

57:17.075 --> 57:19.475
...has changed the way
the government does business.

57:19.644 --> 57:23.944
The Patriot Act allows for searches
of medical and financial records...

57:24.115 --> 57:26.276
...computer and telephone
conversations...

57:26.451 --> 57:30.478
...even for the books you take out of
the library. But people we spoke to...

57:30.655 --> 57:33.988
...say they're willing to give up
liberties to fight terrorism.

57:34.158 --> 57:38.492
- Maybe that's a good thing.
- It's sad, but it has to be done.

57:38.663 --> 57:42.224
Yes, something needed to be done.

57:42.400 --> 57:45.733
These are the good people
who make up Peace Fresno.

57:45.903 --> 57:48.963
A community group
in Fresno, California.

57:49.407 --> 57:52.843
Unlike the rest of us,
they received an early lesson...

57:53.011 --> 57:55.741
...in what the Patriot Act is all about.

57:55.913 --> 58:00.247
Each week, they meet to discuss
matters of peace.

58:00.418 --> 58:05.788
They sit around, they share stories,
they eat cookies.

58:05.957 --> 58:08.551
Some have more than one.

