They got people to believe there was
a threat when in fact there wasn't one.

01:16:31.661 --> 01:16:34.255
You get told things every day
that don't happen.

01:16:34.431 --> 01:16:36.058
It doesn't seem to bother people.

01:16:36.233 --> 01:16:39.134
The Democrats were there to put
a stop to all these falsehoods.

01:16:42.105 --> 01:16:44.073
I'll vote to give the president
authority he needs.

01:16:44.241 --> 01:16:48.371
United States is prepared to lead the
coalition of the willing that will do it.

01:16:48.545 --> 01:16:50.945
When I say we will lead
a coalition of the willing...

01:16:51.114 --> 01:16:53.742
...to disarm him if he chooses
not to disarm, I mean it.

01:16:53.917 --> 01:16:57.683
- Who's in that coalition of the willing?
- You will find out who's in it.

01:16:58.955 --> 01:17:01.480
The coalition of the willing.

01:17:01.658 --> 01:17:02.920
Roll call.

01:17:03.093 --> 01:17:06.085
The Republic of Palau.

01:17:06.263 --> 01:17:10.529
The Republic of Costa Rica.

01:17:10.700 --> 01:17:14.431
The Republic of Iceland.

01:17:14.604 --> 01:17:18.540
None of these countries has an army,
or for that matter, weapons.

01:17:18.708 --> 01:17:22.701
So it looked like we'd be doing
most of the invading stuff ourselves.

01:17:23.914 --> 01:17:27.509
- Then there was also:
- Romania.

01:17:27.684 --> 01:17:32.383
The Kingdom of Morocco.

01:17:32.556 --> 01:17:35.548
Morocco wasn't officially
a member of the coalition...

01:17:35.725 --> 01:17:38.956
...but according to one report, they did
offer to send 2000 monkeys...

01:17:39.129 --> 01:17:41.222
...to help detonate land mines.

01:17:42.799 --> 01:17:44.426
These are men of vision.

01:17:44.601 --> 01:17:46.228
The Netherlands.

01:17:46.403 --> 01:17:48.200
And I'm proud to call them allies.

01:17:49.773 --> 01:17:51.741
Afghanistan.

01:17:51.908 --> 01:17:53.739
Afghanistan?

01:17:53.910 --> 01:17:56.140
Oh, yeah. They had an army.

01:17:56.313 --> 01:18:00.306
Our army. I guess that's one way
to build a coalition.

01:18:00.483 --> 01:18:02.883
Just keep invading countries.

01:18:03.053 --> 01:18:07.319
Yes, with our mighty coalition intact,
we were ready.

01:18:07.490 --> 01:18:11.051
One could almost say
it's the mother of all coalitions.

01:18:13.763 --> 01:18:16.823
Fortunately, we have an independent
media in this country...

01:18:17.000 --> 01:18:18.934
...who would tell us the truth.

01:18:19.102 --> 01:18:23.129
The rallying around the president,
the flag and the troops has begun.

01:18:23.306 --> 01:18:24.830
And we're gonna win!

01:18:25.008 --> 01:18:27.602
You have to be with troops
to understand the adrenaline.

01:18:27.777 --> 01:18:30.245
I want you to know,
I think Navy SEALs rock.

01:18:30.413 --> 01:18:33.439
The pictures you're seeing
are absolutely phenomenal.

01:18:33.617 --> 01:18:38.111
When my country's at war,
I want my country to win.

01:18:38.288 --> 01:18:41.815
Iraqi opposition has faded
in the face of American power.

01:18:41.992 --> 01:18:46.361
What you're watching here is truly
historic television and journalism.

01:18:46.529 --> 01:18:48.019
It was absolutely electrifying.

01:18:48.198 --> 01:18:51.531
They had to strap me in with my
camera at the back of the plane.

01:18:51.701 --> 01:18:54.101
An awesome, synchronized
killing machine.

01:18:54.271 --> 01:18:55.795
There is an inherent bias...

01:18:55.972 --> 01:18:58.634
...in the coverage of the American
press in general.

01:18:58.808 --> 01:19:01.208
Am I slanted and biased?
You damn well bet I am.

01:19:05.515 --> 01:19:08.075
But one story the media
wasn't covering...

01:19:08.251 --> 01:19:10.014
...was the personal story...

01:19:10.186 --> 01:19:13.553
...of each and every soldier
who was killed in the war.

01:19:13.723 --> 01:19:16.191
The government would not allow
any cameras...

01:19:16.359 --> 01:19:18.623
...to show the coffins coming home.

01:19:19.229 --> 01:19:21.925
That kind of story is a downer...

01:19:22.098 --> 01:19:25.966
...especially when you're getting
ready for a party on a boat.

01:20:08.478 --> 01:20:09.706
My fellow Americans...

01:20:11.281 --> 01:20:14.717
...major combat operations
in Iraq have ended.

01:20:14.884 --> 01:20:16.681
In the battle of Iraq...

01:20:16.853 --> 01:20:21.654
...the United States
and our allies have prevailed.

01:20:32.535 --> 01:20:34.526
Get out of the way!

01:20:41.878 --> 01:20:45.211
Move! Move! Move! Move!

01:21:05.101 --> 01:21:08.070
162, the number of troops
killed by hostile fire.

01:21:08.238 --> 01:21:11.935
- 244 U.S. troops...
- 384 U.S. troops lost their lives...

01:21:12.108 --> 01:21:15.043
- Total killed, 484.
- Died in the line of duty, 500...

01:21:15.211 --> 01:21:16.508
631 American troops...

01:21:16.679 --> 01:21:19.011
More than 825 troops
have been killed in Iraq.

01:21:19.182 --> 01:21:21.980
The largest number of American
military deaths since Vietnam.

01:21:22.152 --> 01:21:28.216
There are some who feel like
that if they attack us...

01:21:28.391 --> 01:21:31.019
...that we may decide
to leave prematurely.

01:21:31.795 --> 01:21:34.195
They don't understand,
if that's the case.

01:21:34.364 --> 01:21:36.161
Let me finish.

01:21:37.033 --> 01:21:41.299
There are some who feel like
the conditions are such...

01:21:41.471 --> 01:21:43.268
...that they can attack us there.

01:21:43.440 --> 01:21:45.169
My answer is, bring them on.

01:21:59.222 --> 01:22:01.952
The United States was planning
on walking through here...

01:22:02.125 --> 01:22:04.457
...like it was gonna be easy and all.

01:22:04.627 --> 01:22:07.824
But it's not that easy
to conquer a country, is it?

01:22:14.504 --> 01:22:18.497
The renewed battle for control
of Iraq raged for a fourth day today...

01:22:18.675 --> 01:22:22.008
...with street clashes in nearly
every corner of the country.

01:22:22.178 --> 01:22:24.806
Iraq could become "another Vietnam."

01:22:24.981 --> 01:22:28.382
Officials say they see evidence
that Sunni and Shiite extremists...

01:22:28.551 --> 01:22:30.041
...might be joining forces.

01:22:30.220 --> 01:22:32.313
They're not happy they're occupied.

01:22:33.256 --> 01:22:35.850
I wouldn't be happy
if I were occupied either.

01:22:45.468 --> 01:22:47.766
Two Japanese aid workers
and a journalist...

01:22:47.937 --> 01:22:49.996
...kidnapped by men calling
themselves...

01:22:50.173 --> 01:22:52.038
...the Mujahideen Squadrons.

01:22:52.208 --> 01:22:54.369
They threatened to burn
the hostages alive...

01:22:54.544 --> 01:22:58.776
...if Japan does not withdraw its troops
from Iraq within three days.

01:22:59.382 --> 01:23:00.940
What's happened?

01:23:03.286 --> 01:23:04.583
They attacked our convoy.

01:23:05.555 --> 01:23:06.920
You wanna give us your name?

01:23:07.457 --> 01:23:10.051
Hamill, Thomas.

01:23:11.060 --> 01:23:11.194
The Pentagon might keep up
to 24,000 troops in combat...

01:23:11.194 --> 01:23:14.322
The Pentagon might keep up
to 24,000 troops in combat...

01:23:14.497 --> 01:23:15.759
...beyond their tour.

01:23:15.932 --> 01:23:18.264
I know our numbers
in the military have gone down.

01:23:18.434 --> 01:23:20.197
They talk about retention.

01:23:21.804 --> 01:23:23.965
I never expected
to be deployed this long.

01:23:24.140 --> 01:23:25.437
I don't think anybody did.

01:23:25.808 --> 01:23:28.641
I don't have any clue
as to why we're still in Iraq.

01:23:28.811 --> 01:23:32.212
If Donald Rumsfeld was here,
I'd ask him for his resignation.

01:23:33.483 --> 01:23:35.451
With the war not going
as planned...

01:23:35.985 --> 01:23:38.818
...and the military in need
of many more troops...

01:23:39.622 --> 01:23:42.090
...where would they find
the new recruits?

01:23:42.258 --> 01:23:44.249
Military experts say three times...

01:23:44.427 --> 01:23:46.657
...the 120,000 U.S. troops
now deployed...

01:23:46.829 --> 01:23:50.731
...would be needed to pacify
and rebuild the country.

01:23:51.901 --> 01:23:54.734
They would find them
all across America...

01:23:54.904 --> 01:23:58.601
...in the places that had been
destroyed by the economy.

01:23:59.042 --> 01:24:01.670
Places where one
of the only jobs available...

01:24:01.844 --> 01:24:03.778
...was to join the Army.

01:24:03.947 --> 01:24:07.041
Places like my hometown
of Flint, Michigan.

01:24:07.216 --> 01:24:08.843
I was watching TV one day...

01:24:09.018 --> 01:24:12.954
...and they showed some of the areas
that had been hit by bombs.

01:24:13.122 --> 01:24:15.215
And while watching,
I got to thinking...

01:24:15.391 --> 01:24:17.621
...there's parts of Flint
that look like that.

01:24:17.794 --> 01:24:19.284
And we ain't been in a war.

01:24:19.862 --> 01:24:21.727
Look at the neighborhood I live in.

01:24:21.898 --> 01:24:24.298
Most of them are abandoned.
You know, I mean...

01:24:24.467 --> 01:24:27.095
...that's not right.
You wanna talk about terrorism?

01:24:27.270 --> 01:24:30.603
Come right here. President Bush,
right here. Come right here.

01:24:30.773 --> 01:24:33.173
He knows about this corner.
I e-mailed him.

01:24:34.010 --> 01:24:36.444
At the end of January of '04...

01:24:36.613 --> 01:24:39.377
...the unemployment rate
in Flint was 17 percent.

01:24:39.549 --> 01:24:42.143
But you have to take
into consideration as well...

01:24:42.318 --> 01:24:45.287
...that when your unemployment
runs out you're no longer counted.

01:24:45.455 --> 01:24:48.618
I would say that we're close
to at least 50 percent...

01:24:48.791 --> 01:24:51.589
...not working or underemployed.

01:24:51.761 --> 01:24:54.628
Because being underemployed
is just as dangerous.

01:24:55.231 --> 01:24:57.597
My family has gone through
the welfare system...

01:24:57.767 --> 01:24:59.029
...when it was Job Central.

01:24:59.202 --> 01:25:02.330
In the mid-'80s I came through
the job training partnership program.

01:25:04.941 --> 01:25:06.806
I went to a secretary school.

01:25:06.976 --> 01:25:10.571
Years later, I'm executive assistant
to the president of the agency.

01:25:10.747 --> 01:25:12.339
Interesting.

01:25:12.515 --> 01:25:14.380
My mother used to tell me
all the time:

01:25:14.550 --> 01:25:16.677
"Why do you always go
for the underdog?"

01:25:16.853 --> 01:25:19.083
It was because the underdog
is who needed me.

01:25:19.255 --> 01:25:22.782
People that don't have anything,
that's who I have to fight for.

01:25:22.959 --> 01:25:25.154
And that's who I have fought for
my entire life.

01:25:25.328 --> 01:25:28.229
I started taking my children
and telling my children:

01:25:28.398 --> 01:25:29.922
"The military is a good option.

01:25:30.099 --> 01:25:33.034
I can't afford to have you
go to college. I can't pay your way.

01:25:33.202 --> 01:25:34.794
Financial aid will not help you."

01:25:34.971 --> 01:25:37.405
So I, as a mother,
started teaching my children...

01:25:37.573 --> 01:25:39.768
...about the options
that the military could do.

01:25:39.942 --> 01:25:41.705
They would take them
around the world.

01:25:41.878 --> 01:25:45.075
They'd see all the things that I,
as a mother, couldn't let them see.

01:25:45.248 --> 01:25:49.207
It'd pay for their education that I, as
their mother and father, couldn't pay.

01:25:49.385 --> 01:25:51.876
The military is a good option
for kids in Flint.

01:25:52.055 --> 01:25:55.081
The military is an excellent option
for the people of Flint.

01:25:56.659 --> 01:26:00.254
How many of you have a friend
or a family member in the service?

01:26:01.831 --> 01:26:04.391
Anybody currently serving
overseas?

01:26:04.567 --> 01:26:06.364
- A brother of mine.
- My cousin.

01:26:06.536 --> 01:26:07.798
Yeah, cousin.

01:26:07.970 --> 01:26:09.835
- Where's your brother?
- Iraq.

01:26:10.006 --> 01:26:11.837
Germany.

01:26:12.008 --> 01:26:16.104
My cousin got shipped off
to Iraq, like, three days ago.

01:26:16.279 --> 01:26:17.712
Dang.

01:26:17.880 --> 01:26:20.110
There's, like, an Army
or Navy recruiter...

01:26:20.283 --> 01:26:23.650
...or Marines recruiter up there
almost every week...

01:26:24.353 --> 01:26:28.414
...in the lunchroom recruiting
students at the lunchroom.

01:26:28.991 --> 01:26:32.324
There are people with a calling.

01:26:35.565 --> 01:26:39.899
Most serve one weekend a month
and two weeks a year.

01:26:42.004 --> 01:26:43.665
Earning money for college.

01:26:47.510 --> 01:26:49.842
Protecting their community.

01:26:51.247 --> 01:26:53.579
In the Army National Guard...

01:26:54.083 --> 01:26:55.345
...you can.

01:26:58.354 --> 01:26:59.685
I'm going into the Air Force.

01:26:59.856 --> 01:27:02.882
I'm gonna take a year off
after high school.

01:27:03.059 --> 01:27:06.495
And then make a career. I wanna be
an aircraft maintenance technician.

01:27:06.662 --> 01:27:09.722
I ran into a recruiter, and there
was something I noticed about it.

01:27:09.899 --> 01:27:12.595
And this is kind of on another...
I noticed it was odd.

01:27:12.769 --> 01:27:15.465
More like he was hiring me
than recruiting me for the Army.

01:27:15.638 --> 01:27:18.766
It was the way he approached me.
I was in Borders Books and Music.

01:27:18.941 --> 01:27:21.205
He came up like he was handing
us a business card.

01:27:21.377 --> 01:27:23.868
He had business cards
made for the Army.

01:27:29.252 --> 01:27:31.812
Meet Marine Staff
Sergeant Dale Kortman...

01:27:31.988 --> 01:27:34.013
...and Sergeant Raymond Plouhar.

01:27:35.124 --> 01:27:39.185
They are two of the many recruiters
assigned to Flint, Michigan.

01:27:39.529 --> 01:27:41.588
They're very busy these days.

01:27:41.764 --> 01:27:43.755
Look, he's running away already.

01:27:43.933 --> 01:27:46.595
- He's seen us coming.
- Yeah.

01:27:47.436 --> 01:27:49.028
What have we got here?

01:27:49.205 --> 01:27:51.469
- Need a little gangster.
- Yeah.

01:27:51.974 --> 01:27:54.704
We're heading over
to the Courtland Mall right now.

01:27:55.812 --> 01:27:57.712
They decided not to go
to the wealthier...

01:27:57.880 --> 01:28:00.212
...Genesee Valley Mall
in the suburbs.

01:28:00.383 --> 01:28:03.250
They have a hard time
recruiting young people there.

01:28:03.419 --> 01:28:06.752
Instead, they went
to the other mall.

01:28:06.923 --> 01:28:09.585
- Let's go in through Mervyn's.
- In through Mervyn's.

01:28:09.759 --> 01:28:13.593
And then we'll walk straight down
and straight back and then go down...

01:28:13.963 --> 01:28:15.988
Gents, you know
we're looking at you, right?

01:28:16.165 --> 01:28:17.826
You guys ever think
about joining up?

01:28:18.000 --> 01:28:20.594
I thought about going to college
and playing basketball.

01:28:20.770 --> 01:28:23.170
- You any good?
- Yeah. Especially basketball.

01:28:23.339 --> 01:28:25.466
Good. You can play ball
for the Marine Corps.

01:28:25.641 --> 01:28:28.474
Travel around the world
for the Corps basketball team.

01:28:28.644 --> 01:28:31.078
- David Robinson was in the military.
- Oh, was he?

01:28:31.247 --> 01:28:33.010
Yeah, you can definitely hook it up.

01:28:33.182 --> 01:28:36.674
Right now somebody out there wants
to be a Marine but has no idea how to.

01:28:36.853 --> 01:28:39.048
- Where you work at?
- I work at KFC.

01:28:39.222 --> 01:28:42.350
- Sweet. Hook us up with deals.
- Yes.

01:28:42.525 --> 01:28:44.288
They're waiting to get recruited.

01:28:44.460 --> 01:28:46.621
I was gonna try a career
in music or something.

01:28:46.796 --> 01:28:50.061
Career in music? Maybe we can
get you a career in music.

01:28:50.233 --> 01:28:53.100
Let the Marines go for it.
I'm sure you know who Shaggy is.

01:28:53.603 --> 01:28:57.437
- You know anything about him?
- Yeah, he's the Jamaican singer.

01:28:57.607 --> 01:28:59.632
How about a former Marine?

01:28:59.809 --> 01:29:01.367
- Oh.
- Did you know it?

01:29:01.544 --> 01:29:04.240
You need to know discipline
if you're gonna get into music.

01:29:04.413 --> 01:29:06.176
Especially discipline
with the money.

01:29:06.349 --> 01:29:08.749
If you make a million, you need
to manage that money.

01:29:08.918 --> 01:29:10.510
Come to the office, we can talk...

01:29:10.686 --> 01:29:12.620
...show you everything
about the Marines.

01:29:12.788 --> 01:29:15.086
- A plan?
- What you got going this afternoon?

01:29:15.258 --> 01:29:17.988
How about tomorrow?
10:00 Monday morning?

01:29:18.160 --> 01:29:21.061
- That sounds pretty good.
- You want me to pick you up?

01:29:21.230 --> 01:29:23.790
It's better to get them
when they're in ones and twos...

01:29:23.966 --> 01:29:25.661
...and work on them that way.

01:29:25.835 --> 01:29:27.063
Ladies, ready to join up?

01:29:27.236 --> 01:29:29.261
Green hat right behind us.

01:29:29.438 --> 01:29:33.101
- Looks young. He's young.
- Yeah.

01:29:33.276 --> 01:29:35.506
We got two over here...

01:29:35.678 --> 01:29:37.543
...right over by the red van.

01:29:37.713 --> 01:29:39.840
You go that way, I go this way,
we corner them.

01:29:40.016 --> 01:29:42.007
- You're in the ninth grade?
- Yes, sir.

01:29:42.184 --> 01:29:44.982
Man, you look older
than ninth grade.

01:29:45.154 --> 01:29:46.849
All right, here's my card.

01:29:47.023 --> 01:29:48.991
You ever thought about
being a Marine, man?

01:29:49.158 --> 01:29:51.490
I've thought about it.
I've got a wife and kid now.

01:29:51.661 --> 01:29:53.322
Even more reason to join up.

01:29:53.496 --> 01:29:55.123
What I want to do, man...

01:29:55.298 --> 01:29:58.324
...is get information from you
so I can scratch you off my list...

01:29:58.501 --> 01:30:02.130
...saying I've talked to you, and
you're not interested. Is that cool?

01:30:02.305 --> 01:30:04.705
What's your name? Phone number?
What's your address?

01:30:04.874 --> 01:30:06.273
Add another one to the list.

01:30:06.442 --> 01:30:11.038
However, one would love to have
that chance to experience college life.

01:30:11.213 --> 01:30:14.341
You know, stuff young people
can do without having the risk...

01:30:14.517 --> 01:30:17.782
...of dying in the process,
I guess I can say candidly.

01:30:20.056 --> 01:30:24.390
The holidays add a bit more friction,
as opposed to just another night...

01:30:24.560 --> 01:30:28.724
...in the fact we wanna give our guys
a little time off, time to relax.

01:30:28.898 --> 01:30:32.857
However, we are in a combat zone,
and my soldiers do recognize that fact.

01:30:33.035 --> 01:30:36.129
Everybody's a little bit
nervous about it, I guess.

01:30:36.305 --> 01:30:39.274
We're professionals.
We're gonna take care of you.

01:30:40.343 --> 01:30:42.277
I promise.

01:30:43.412 --> 01:30:47.314
Every house here has the right
to have weapons.

01:30:47.483 --> 01:30:49.713
Maximum, one AK-47.

01:30:49.885 --> 01:30:52.752
We always expect the targets
to be armed.

01:30:59.261 --> 01:31:01.320
Rock 'n' roll.

01:31:03.165 --> 01:31:06.100
These are fucking bolt cutters.

01:31:06.268 --> 01:31:08.566
This goddamn thing
to pry doors open.

01:31:08.738 --> 01:31:10.672
Pop this in there...

01:31:47.343 --> 01:31:49.277
Hey, Adele, just hold up.

01:31:55.918 --> 01:31:57.510
No, no, no, no.

01:31:57.686 --> 01:31:59.347
Where's she going?

01:32:00.122 --> 01:32:01.851
- I'll go with her.
- Where's she going?

01:32:02.024 --> 01:32:03.286
She's gonna call him.

01:32:03.459 --> 01:32:07.327
She's gonna call him? No, no, no.
Where is he at right now?

01:32:07.496 --> 01:32:09.327
Not on the phone.
Not on the phone.

01:32:09.498 --> 01:32:12.558
Is he in the house?
Is he in the house?

01:32:12.735 --> 01:32:15.067
- Passerelli! Passerelli!
- Is he in the house?

01:32:15.237 --> 01:32:17.467
He is? He is in the house? Where?

01:32:17.640 --> 01:32:19.801
- This is him?
- Get up there, second floor!

01:32:19.975 --> 01:32:22.967
Watch out. Go, go, go!
Watch out, Adele, watch out.

01:32:23.145 --> 01:32:24.908
I have one coming up.

01:32:27.416 --> 01:32:30.010
That's Suheib Al Douri?

01:32:31.053 --> 01:32:32.782
- What's your name?
- Suheib.

01:32:32.955 --> 01:32:35.355
- This is Suheib. Yeah.
- This is Suheib.

01:32:35.524 --> 01:32:37.389
- This is Suheib?
- Yeah.

01:32:38.227 --> 01:32:40.218
Stand him up. Get up.

01:32:44.200 --> 01:32:49.263
Tell them to calm down, please.
We will not be long.

01:32:53.042 --> 01:32:55.442
We appreciate your cooperation.
This is the target.

01:32:55.611 --> 01:32:58.136
Suheib Al Douri. Bring him out.

01:32:58.314 --> 01:33:00.680
We have to, as you go back
to the old saying...

01:33:00.850 --> 01:33:03.512
...win the hearts and minds
of the people. That's our job.

01:33:03.686 --> 01:33:06.849
We have to... We have to bring the...

01:33:07.022 --> 01:33:10.321
The ideal of democracy
and freedom to the country...

01:33:10.493 --> 01:33:14.224
...and show them that the American
people are not here to rule Iraq.

01:33:32.915 --> 01:33:36.681
I start doing evidence turn-in.
That process takes about three hours.

01:33:36.852 --> 01:33:38.649
So that's gonna be it for the night.

01:33:38.821 --> 01:33:41.915
That concludes Christmas Eve.

01:33:45.327 --> 01:33:47.158
Merry Christmas, PRT.
Merry Christmas.

01:33:47.329 --> 01:33:49.456
Santa came to Iraq
just for you guys.

01:33:49.632 --> 01:33:51.566
Trying to keep skies
clear for you, Santa.

01:33:54.103 --> 01:33:56.128
Do you consider yourself
a proud American?

01:33:56.305 --> 01:33:57.567
Absolutely.

01:33:57.740 --> 01:34:01.107
I'm an extremely proud American.
I'm probably more proud...

01:34:01.277 --> 01:34:02.539
...than the average Joe.

01:34:02.711 --> 01:34:06.238
When I put my flag out,
I can't allow it to touch the ground.

01:34:06.415 --> 01:34:09.873
Because I know the lives that were lost
and the blood that was shed...

01:34:10.052 --> 01:34:12.020
...so that I could be here
and have a flag.

01:34:12.188 --> 01:34:15.589
- How often do you put the flag out?
- Every single day. Every day.

01:34:15.758 --> 01:34:18.750
I started when my daughter
was in Desert Storm.

01:34:18.928 --> 01:34:20.452
I had the same flag...

01:34:20.629 --> 01:34:24.065
...flying on my front porch
and the same yellow ribbons.

01:34:24.233 --> 01:34:27.259
Praying and hoping every day
that my child would come home safe.

01:34:27.436 --> 01:34:29.461
And everybody's child
would come home safe.

01:34:29.638 --> 01:34:31.299
- And she did.
- And she did.

01:34:31.473 --> 01:34:33.703
Have other family members
been in the military?

01:34:33.876 --> 01:34:35.468
Absolutely. Uncles, aunts...

01:34:37.112 --> 01:34:38.739
...cousins, brothers, father.

01:34:38.914 --> 01:34:40.882
- Very strong military family.
- Very strong.

01:34:41.050 --> 01:34:44.281
My family was...
My family is what I consider...

01:34:44.453 --> 01:34:46.250
...part of the backbone of America.

01:34:46.422 --> 01:34:48.913
It's families like mine.
And it's not just my family.

01:34:49.091 --> 01:34:51.651
There's hundreds of families,
millions of families...

01:34:51.827 --> 01:34:54.227
...that this country was founded
on their backs.

01:34:54.396 --> 01:34:57.854
I have been known to be
a conservative Democrat. Yeah.

01:34:58.033 --> 01:35:00.092
That's what you consider
yourself? Yeah.

01:35:00.269 --> 01:35:03.602
- Yeah, it's a great country.
- It's a great country. A great country.

01:35:03.772 --> 01:35:08.573
The cross that I choose to wear
is a multicultural, multicolor cross.

01:35:08.744 --> 01:35:11.941
That's because I believe that all
God's people come in many colors.

01:35:12.114 --> 01:35:14.514
And my family itself is multicultural.

01:35:15.050 --> 01:35:18.417
You have a daughter
who went into the military.

01:35:18.587 --> 01:35:20.817
Then your first-born son,
in the military.

01:35:20.990 --> 01:35:26.451
That's quite a gift to the country
from your family.

01:35:26.629 --> 01:35:29.097
So having a son in the Army,
pretty proud thing.

01:35:29.265 --> 01:35:32.496
Oh, you know what? He made it.

01:35:33.002 --> 01:35:37.666
What was your reaction to protestors
during the Gulf War or Vietnam?

01:35:37.840 --> 01:35:39.603
I always hated the protestors.

01:35:39.775 --> 01:35:43.871
I always hated the protestors.
It was just a slap in my face.

01:35:44.046 --> 01:35:48.039
It was just like they were
dishonoring my son.

01:35:48.217 --> 01:35:51.948
And I burned in my soul
to tell them, "You don't understand.

01:35:52.121 --> 01:35:54.282
They're not there because
they wanna be there."

01:35:54.456 --> 01:35:58.017
But then I came to understand
they weren't protesting the men...

01:35:58.193 --> 01:36:02.129
...and women there. They were
protesting the concept of the war.

01:36:02.298 --> 01:36:05.267
I know I'm a soldier,
and I'm here to do a job.

01:36:06.135 --> 01:36:08.763
I've been a soldier for a while.

01:36:10.139 --> 01:36:13.108
Once you have to go
and do your job...

01:36:13.275 --> 01:36:15.641
...and you see the things
that you see...

01:36:17.613 --> 01:36:20.411
...I was saying, there's some
disillusionment in that.

01:36:20.582 --> 01:36:25.019
Battalion commander fully
expects us to be...

01:36:25.187 --> 01:36:28.020
...attacked in some type of way...

01:36:28.190 --> 01:36:30.283
...before we get to FARP Shell.

01:36:31.193 --> 01:36:34.128
I know that so far
it's been pretty calm.

01:36:34.296 --> 01:36:35.661
Not much has happened.

01:36:35.831 --> 01:36:40.666
But be aware that it can,
and it probably will.

01:36:45.174 --> 01:36:48.109
They're beginning to organize
themselves, just in neighborhoods.

01:36:48.277 --> 01:36:51.644
The kids get together a lot.
Well, I can't say kids...

01:36:51.814 --> 01:36:53.338
...but guys about 17, 18...

01:36:53.515 --> 01:36:55.073
...starting to come together.

01:36:55.250 --> 01:36:57.684
They hate us.
Why, I'm not really sure.

01:37:00.422 --> 01:37:04.449
Immoral behavior
breeds immoral behavior.

01:37:05.194 --> 01:37:07.560
When a president commits
the immoral act...

01:37:07.730 --> 01:37:12.064
...of sending otherwise good kids
to war based on a lie...

01:37:12.234 --> 01:37:14.065
...this is what you get.

01:37:14.236 --> 01:37:16.727
Hey, is he ticklish?

01:37:16.905 --> 01:37:18.736
Don't tell me you don't know.

01:37:38.994 --> 01:37:42.088
To have these people
shoot at us, kill us, blow us up...

01:37:42.264 --> 01:37:44.289
...whatever, means they can.

01:37:44.466 --> 01:37:46.093
And I don't understand it.

01:37:46.268 --> 01:37:48.862
We're trying to help these people,
and it seems...

01:37:49.037 --> 01:37:51.198
...they don't want our help.
"Get out of here!"

01:37:51.373 --> 01:37:54.137
The minute something goes wrong,
"Why weren't you here?

01:37:54.309 --> 01:37:56.368
Why didn't you do this?"
You know, it's...

01:37:56.545 --> 01:37:58.570
I hate this country.

01:37:58.747 --> 01:38:02.808
You know, you... I feel
that a part of your soul...

01:38:03.685 --> 01:38:08.145
...is destroyed in taking another life.

01:38:09.558 --> 01:38:12.356
Yeah, that statement is very true.

01:38:12.528 --> 01:38:16.020
You cannot kill someone
without killing a part of yourself.

01:38:16.465 --> 01:38:17.727
If you get called up...

01:38:17.900 --> 01:38:19.731
...will you go back to Iraq?
- No.

01:38:21.870 --> 01:38:24.964
What repercussions
do you face if you don't?

01:38:25.140 --> 01:38:26.664
Possible jail time.

01:38:26.842 --> 01:38:28.309
That's one possible thing.

01:38:28.477 --> 01:38:31.139
- Are you willing to risk that?
- Yes.

01:38:31.313 --> 01:38:32.974
Yes, l...

01:38:33.148 --> 01:38:36.914
I will not let my person...

01:38:38.187 --> 01:38:41.384
I will not let anyone...

01:38:41.557 --> 01:38:44.993
...send me back over there
to kill other poor people.

01:38:45.160 --> 01:38:50.792
Especially when they pose
no threat to me and my country.

01:38:54.937 --> 01:38:56.598
I won't do it.

01:38:57.606 --> 01:39:00.302
This is an impressive crowd.
The haves...

01:39:00.476 --> 01:39:02.808
...and the have-mores.

01:39:04.680 --> 01:39:07.080
Some people call you the elite.

01:39:07.249 --> 01:39:09.513
I call you my base.

01:39:17.392 --> 01:39:19.883
While Bush was busy
taking care of his base...

01:39:20.062 --> 01:39:22.257
...and professing his love
for our troops...

01:39:22.431 --> 01:39:26.561
...he proposed cutting combat
soldiers' pay by 33 percent...

01:39:26.735 --> 01:39:29.499
...and assistance to their families
by 60 percent.

01:39:30.072 --> 01:39:31.505
He opposed giving veterans...

01:39:31.673 --> 01:39:34.665
...a billion dollars more
in health-care benefits...

01:39:34.843 --> 01:39:37.903
...and he supported
closing veteran hospitals.

01:39:38.080 --> 01:39:41.538
He tried to double the prescription
drug costs for veterans...

01:39:41.717 --> 01:39:45.414
...and opposed full benefits
for part-time reservists.

01:39:46.355 --> 01:39:48.755
When Staff Sergeant Brett Petriken
from Flint...

01:39:48.924 --> 01:39:51.518
...was killed in Iraq on May 26th...

01:39:51.693 --> 01:39:54.093
...the Army sent his last paycheck
to his family...

01:39:54.263 --> 01:39:57.858
...but they docked him for the last five
days of the month he didn't work...

01:39:58.033 --> 01:39:59.364
...because he was dead.

01:40:01.703 --> 01:40:04.171
They say they're not gonna leave
any veteran behind...

01:40:04.339 --> 01:40:06.739
...but they're leaving all kinds
of veterans behind.

01:40:09.244 --> 01:40:11.906
To say we're forgotten,
I know we're not. But missed? Yes.

01:40:12.080 --> 01:40:14.878
Yes. There's a lot of soldiers
that have been missed...

01:40:15.050 --> 01:40:16.915
...that have been skipped over.

01:40:17.085 --> 01:40:19.144
Didn't get the proper coverage
they deserved.

01:40:19.321 --> 01:40:22.381
There's a death toll, but not
showing the injured or amputated.

01:40:25.594 --> 01:40:28.062
- I still feel like I have hands.
- Yeah.

01:40:28.230 --> 01:40:32.462
And the pain is like my hands
are being crushed in a vise.

01:40:32.634 --> 01:40:34.431
But they do a lot to help it...

01:40:34.603 --> 01:40:36.571
...and they take a lot
of the edge off it.

01:40:36.738 --> 01:40:39.605
It makes it a lot more tolerable.

01:40:40.208 --> 01:40:42.904
I was injured in late April
on patrol in Baghdad.

01:40:46.048 --> 01:40:49.347
A couple of guys come out
and ambushed us.

01:40:49.518 --> 01:40:51.952
I got nerve damage
and stuff like that.

01:40:52.120 --> 01:40:56.420
I've got a lot of pain.
I'm constantly in pain.

01:40:57.159 --> 01:40:59.184
I take a lot of morphine...

01:40:59.361 --> 01:41:02.728
...to help with that and stuff.

01:41:03.599 --> 01:41:04.930
I'm doing...

01:41:05.100 --> 01:41:07.568
Doing... You know, just readjusting.

01:41:07.736 --> 01:41:11.228
Getting life back on track.

01:41:11.406 --> 01:41:14.068
You know what I'm saying?

01:41:14.242 --> 01:41:17.302
I'm not gonna do what it is
that I did before.

01:41:18.313 --> 01:41:21.510
I was a Republican
for quite a few years.

01:41:21.683 --> 01:41:23.275
And...

01:41:24.920 --> 01:41:27.081
...for some reason, they...

01:41:29.825 --> 01:41:32.350
They conduct business
in a very dishonest way.

01:41:32.527 --> 01:41:35.360
I'm gonna be incredibly active
in the Democratic Party...

01:41:35.530 --> 01:41:38.556
...down where I live once I get out.

01:41:39.001 --> 01:41:41.060
I'm gonna definitely do my best...

01:41:41.236 --> 01:41:44.364
...to ensure that the Democrats
win control.

01:41:44.539 --> 01:41:47.508
Iraq, Baghdad, I didn't know
anything of those things.

01:41:50.445 --> 01:41:54.472
And we were in the hallway
in the upstairs of our house...

01:41:54.650 --> 01:41:57.380
...and he was crying and said
that he was really scared.

01:41:57.552 --> 01:41:59.918
And he didn't want
to have to go to Iraq.

01:42:00.088 --> 01:42:04.286
So we had a conversation about,
sometimes some fear is healthy...

01:42:04.459 --> 01:42:06.484
...because it keeps
our senses about us.

01:42:06.662 --> 01:42:08.994
That's when he told me
he hadn't told anybody else.

01:42:09.164 --> 01:42:11.359
But he knew he was going
to Baghdad.

01:42:13.669 --> 01:42:17.765
We were... As everybody,
we were glued to the TV.

01:42:17.939 --> 01:42:20.908
Just glued, completely glued
to the television...

01:42:21.076 --> 01:42:22.873
...in hopes of seeing
a glimpse of him.

01:42:23.045 --> 01:42:25.309
"Can't you please go to
where the helicopters are?

01:42:25.480 --> 01:42:27.505
Can't you please let us see him?"

01:42:27.683 --> 01:42:30.379
Then that night,
it was about 10 something...

01:42:30.552 --> 01:42:33.077
...I went upstairs to the bedroom.

01:42:33.255 --> 01:42:35.849
I was in bed, flipping the channels
with the remote.

01:42:36.024 --> 01:42:39.460
All I heard was, "Black Hawk down,
South Central Iraq."

01:42:39.628 --> 01:42:42.620
What I can tell you at this hour
is that last night...

01:42:42.798 --> 01:42:45.961
...the Army did, indeed, lose
a Black Hawk helicopter.

01:42:46.134 --> 01:42:48.694
We are being told by officers
on the ground...

01:42:48.870 --> 01:42:51.600
...that there were six occupants
inside the Black Hawk.

01:42:51.773 --> 01:42:53.900
The next morning
I got up, and I said:

01:42:54.076 --> 01:42:56.408
"You push those sad thoughts
out of your mind.

01:42:56.578 --> 01:42:58.375
Okay, Jesus,
I need you to come in.

01:42:58.547 --> 01:43:01.175
I need you, Jesus.
You gotta help me through this."

01:43:01.349 --> 01:43:04.841
The Army called me, and I remember
getting on the phone and him saying...

01:43:05.020 --> 01:43:07.955
Asking me was I Lila Lipscomb,
and I said, "Yes."

01:43:08.123 --> 01:43:11.024
And he said, "Mother of
Sergeant Michael Pedersen?"

01:43:12.661 --> 01:43:15.630
And I remember
dropping the telephone.

01:43:18.667 --> 01:43:21.397
And all I can honestly say
that I remember...

01:43:21.570 --> 01:43:24.232
...is, "Ma'am,
the United States Army...

01:43:24.406 --> 01:43:28.502
...the secretary of defense
regretfully informs you..."

01:43:30.879 --> 01:43:32.779
That's all I know.

01:43:34.015 --> 01:43:37.815
The grief grabbed me so hard...

01:43:37.986 --> 01:43:40.454
...that I literally fell on the floor.

01:43:40.622 --> 01:43:43.989
And I was alone. I didn't
have anybody to pick me up.

01:43:44.159 --> 01:43:47.925
So I literally crawled
over to my desk...

01:43:48.096 --> 01:43:49.563
...and was hanging on.

01:43:49.731 --> 01:43:52.029
And I remember screaming:

01:43:52.200 --> 01:43:54.168
"Why does it have to be Michael?

01:43:54.336 --> 01:43:59.774
Why did you have to take my son?
Why is it my son you had to take?

01:43:59.941 --> 01:44:01.841
He didn't do anything.

01:44:02.010 --> 01:44:04.740
He wasn't a bad guy.
He was a good guy.

01:44:04.913 --> 01:44:06.972
Why did you have to take my son?"

01:44:07.949 --> 01:44:10.918
l... l... l... I'm...

01:44:11.086 --> 01:44:14.146
I can't imagine what it must be like
to lose a son or a daughter...

01:44:14.322 --> 01:44:16.882
...or a husband and...
Or a wife, for that matter.

01:44:17.058 --> 01:44:19.549
And l... It pains me.

01:44:21.062 --> 01:44:22.996
Do you have his last letter?

01:44:23.165 --> 01:44:25.065
It was mailed March 16th...

01:44:25.734 --> 01:44:29.670
...but I didn't get it until probably
a week before he was killed.

01:44:30.272 --> 01:44:32.035
"Hello. Hey, Mama.

01:44:32.207 --> 01:44:35.438
Well, sorry I haven't
been able to call.

01:44:35.610 --> 01:44:37.874
They took the phone
seven days ago.

01:44:38.046 --> 01:44:40.037
I got the letter and box.

01:44:40.215 --> 01:44:44.117
That is so cool.
Your first grandson came...

01:44:45.420 --> 01:44:47.980
...the same day your oldest son did.

01:44:48.156 --> 01:44:50.556
How is everyone? I'm doing fine.

01:44:50.725 --> 01:44:54.855
We are just out here in the sand
and windstorms waiting.

01:44:55.030 --> 01:44:57.794
What in the world is wrong
with George?

01:44:57.966 --> 01:45:00.867
Trying to be like his dad, Bush.

01:45:01.036 --> 01:45:03.800
He got us out here
for nothing whatsoever.

01:45:03.972 --> 01:45:07.237
I am so furious right now, Mama.

01:45:07.976 --> 01:45:13.107
I really hope they do not
re-elect that fool, honestly.

01:45:13.281 --> 01:45:16.079
I am in good spirits,
and I am doing okay.

01:45:16.251 --> 01:45:18.014
I really miss you guys.

01:45:18.186 --> 01:45:20.154
Thanks for the Bible...

01:45:21.823 --> 01:45:24.451
...and books and candy.

01:45:24.626 --> 01:45:28.756
I really look forward to letters
from you guys.

01:45:28.930 --> 01:45:33.162
Well, tell all the family hello
and that I am doing fine.

01:45:33.335 --> 01:45:36.771
We don't expect anything
to happen any time soon.

01:45:36.938 --> 01:45:41.136
I cannot wait to get home
and get back to my life.

01:45:41.309 --> 01:45:43.436
Tell Sputnik congrats...

01:45:43.612 --> 01:45:47.275
...and I'll see my first nephew soon...

01:45:48.049 --> 01:45:50.313
...as soon as I get back
to the States.

01:45:50.919 --> 01:45:53.012
Hope you guys are doing okay...

01:45:53.188 --> 01:45:55.179
...and keep sending the mail.

01:45:55.357 --> 01:45:58.690
It makes getting through
the days easier.

01:46:01.296 --> 01:46:04.231
Well, I am on my way to bed...

01:46:04.399 --> 01:46:07.891
...so I will write you guys soon.

01:46:08.069 --> 01:46:10.196
I love and miss...

01:46:10.372 --> 01:46:12.499
...all of you guys."

01:46:25.120 --> 01:46:27.452
I want him to be alive...

01:46:27.622 --> 01:46:30.420
...and I can't make him alive.

01:46:31.493 --> 01:46:34.360
But your flesh just aches.

01:46:34.529 --> 01:46:37.020
You want your child.
It's out of sync.

01:46:37.198 --> 01:46:41.100
A parent is not supposed
to bury their child.

01:46:43.838 --> 01:46:47.774
I feel... I feel sad for my family...

01:46:47.943 --> 01:46:50.275
...because we lost our son.

01:46:51.646 --> 01:46:53.341
But...

01:46:53.515 --> 01:46:56.678
...I really feel sorry
for the other families...

01:46:56.851 --> 01:47:01.914
...that is losing their kids
as we speak.

01:47:04.159 --> 01:47:06.024
And for what?

01:47:06.194 --> 01:47:07.991
l... I don't...

01:47:09.130 --> 01:47:12.190
That's the...
I guess the sickening part.

01:47:12.367 --> 01:47:13.664
For what?

01:47:14.069 --> 01:47:16.196
You've heard a lot
about Halliburton lately.

01:47:17.806 --> 01:47:21.333
Criticism is okay. We can take it.
Criticism is not failure.

01:47:21.509 --> 01:47:23.636
Our employees are doing
a great job.

01:47:23.812 --> 01:47:26.872
We're feeding the soldiers.
We're rebuilding Iraq.

01:47:27.048 --> 01:47:30.245
Will things go wrong?
Sure they will. It's a war zone.

01:47:30.418 --> 01:47:32.886
We're serving the troops
because of what we know...

01:47:33.054 --> 01:47:34.521
...not who we know.

01:47:34.689 --> 01:47:37.749
Let me tell you about Halliburton,
the company I ran.

01:47:39.361 --> 01:47:41.192
I'm proud of what I did at Halliburton.

01:47:41.363 --> 01:47:44.526
The people are proud of what
they've accomplished. I, frankly...

01:47:44.699 --> 01:47:46.667
...don't feel any need to apologize...

01:47:46.835 --> 01:47:49.736
...for the way I've spent my time
over the last five years...

01:47:49.904 --> 01:47:52.634
...as the CEO and chairman
of a major American corporation.

01:47:52.807 --> 01:47:55.503
This is also an attempt
to divert attention...

01:47:55.677 --> 01:47:58.771
...from the fact they have
no energy policy.

01:47:58.947 --> 01:48:02.246
And as the secretary of energy said,
"We were caught unawares."

01:48:04.486 --> 01:48:09.014
In the middle of the war, Microsoft,
DHL and other corporations...

01:48:09.190 --> 01:48:11.351
...invited Halliburton
to a conference...

01:48:11.526 --> 01:48:15.326
...to figure out how much money
could be made in Iraq.

01:48:16.431 --> 01:48:18.262
Having worked this...

01:48:20.368 --> 01:48:24.566
...effort, even since before the...
The invasion...

01:48:24.739 --> 01:48:27.401
...the liberation of Iraq started.

01:48:27.575 --> 01:48:32.410
You, industry, are definitely
a vital part of that effort.

01:48:32.580 --> 01:48:35.640
We appreciate your interest
in this. We need you.

01:48:35.817 --> 01:48:37.978
Lots of you are small businesses
and struggling:

01:48:39.687 --> 01:48:42.485
"How do we get a piece of this?
You big guys are gonna get it.

01:48:42.657 --> 01:48:46.149
The rest of us will have subcontracting
capability or none at all."

01:48:46.327 --> 01:48:48.591
USTDA is for you.

01:48:48.763 --> 01:48:50.526
Once that oil starts flowing...

01:48:50.698 --> 01:48:52.757
...and money coming,
gonna be lots of money.

01:48:52.934 --> 01:48:55.334
It's the second-largest
reserve of oil in the world.

01:48:55.503 --> 01:48:57.232
No question of how much
money's there.

01:48:57.405 --> 01:49:00.374
I've been getting complaints
from Iraqi firms and American firms.

01:49:02.877 --> 01:49:04.936
The lack of transparency,
the corruption.

01:49:05.113 --> 01:49:09.812
I think the profits American companies
are making, the main companies...

01:49:09.984 --> 01:49:11.246
...are so overwhelming.

01:49:11.419 --> 01:49:14.877
I mean, when you have a line item
for a million dollars...

01:49:15.056 --> 01:49:18.253
...and you subcontract it out
for 50 or 60 or $ 70,000...

01:49:18.426 --> 01:49:19.688
...that's a huge profit.

01:49:19.861 --> 01:49:22.261
It's the American taxpayer
that's gonna pay for that.

01:49:22.430 --> 01:49:25.797
And it's gonna get better.
Start building relationships.

01:49:25.967 --> 01:49:27.798
Because it's gonna get
much better...

01:49:27.969 --> 01:49:30.369
...as the oil flows
and their budgets increase.

01:49:30.538 --> 01:49:33.371
Good news is, whatever it costs,
the government will pay you.

01:49:33.541 --> 01:49:36.374
War is always good
for certain companies...

01:49:36.544 --> 01:49:38.774
...that are in the war...
The business of war.

01:49:41.549 --> 01:49:43.107
We're very proud.

01:49:44.786 --> 01:49:46.583
Supporting U.S. government
and military.

01:49:46.754 --> 01:49:49.348
The real heroes of the campaign
and the reconstruction...

01:49:49.524 --> 01:49:51.890
...are the men and women
of the U.S. Armed Forces.

01:49:52.060 --> 01:49:54.620
We're proud of being any part
we can in supporting them.

01:49:54.796 --> 01:49:58.823
Halliburton delivers hot meals,
supplies, clean clothing...

01:49:59.000 --> 01:50:01.491
...and communications
to our soldiers...

01:50:01.669 --> 01:50:05.901
...so they can be
a little closer to home.

01:50:07.242 --> 01:50:08.709
It's a girl!

01:50:08.877 --> 01:50:11.869
Halliburton. Proud to serve
our troops.

01:50:12.046 --> 01:50:15.447
I just read in the paper
Halliburton got another contract.

01:50:15.617 --> 01:50:18.518
- Halliburton got another contract.
- That's right.

01:50:18.686 --> 01:50:21.280
Which is not being...

01:50:22.524 --> 01:50:23.855
...contested at all.

01:50:24.025 --> 01:50:25.424
Because nobody knows.

01:50:25.593 --> 01:50:28.153
Well, it's in the paper,
so somebody knows.

01:50:28.329 --> 01:50:32.390
But that's after it happens,
after the fact. It's too late.

01:50:33.368 --> 01:50:37.498
The United States is now a major
player in the Iraqi oil business.

01:50:37.672 --> 01:50:39.765
American troops
guard the oil fields...

01:50:39.941 --> 01:50:43.035
...as Texas oil workers
assess their potential.

01:50:43.211 --> 01:50:46.772
It's a safe environment to work in.
We don't feel any risk.

01:50:46.948 --> 01:50:49.883
We feel we're being well protected
here, or we wouldn't be here.

01:50:50.051 --> 01:50:51.313
It's no secret. I mean...

01:50:51.486 --> 01:50:55.616
...I make anywhere between
2 and 3000 a month.

01:50:55.790 --> 01:50:58.020
A Halliburton employee
out here driving a bus...

01:50:58.193 --> 01:51:01.560
...can make between 8 and 10,000
a month. Explain that one to me.

01:51:01.729 --> 01:51:03.219
For 40 hours a week.

01:51:03.398 --> 01:51:05.457
Driving the same
two-and-half-mile route.

01:51:05.633 --> 01:51:06.964
Go figure.

01:51:07.135 --> 01:51:09.228
Where's the justification in that?

01:51:09.404 --> 01:51:12.339
There's no other single area
of the world today...

01:51:14.042 --> 01:51:16.442
...with the opportunity
for business, new business...

01:51:16.611 --> 01:51:19.580
...similar to the opportunity
that's available today in Iraq.

01:51:19.747 --> 01:51:21.544
The president went in,
did what he did.

01:51:23.151 --> 01:51:24.743
We're supporting him
and our troops.

01:51:24.919 --> 01:51:29.515
We wanna make sure
that the efforts and the lost lives...

01:51:29.691 --> 01:51:31.158
...wasn't for no reason.

01:51:31.326 --> 01:51:33.760
If it wasn't for the oil,
nobody would be there.

01:51:33.928 --> 01:51:35.589
Nobody would worry about it.

01:51:35.763 --> 01:51:37.788
Unfortunately,
at least for the near term...

01:51:39.734 --> 01:51:42.760
...we think it's gonna be a good
situation, a dangerous situation.

01:51:42.937 --> 01:51:45.497
Good for business,
bad for the people.

01:51:45.673 --> 01:51:49.131
Today on the news,
Rumsfeld was saying...

01:51:49.310 --> 01:51:53.246
And Wolfowitz was saying:

01:51:53.414 --> 01:51:56.941
"The Iraqi people are much,
much better off.

01:51:57.118 --> 01:52:00.212
Isn't it better that we
got rid of Saddam...

01:52:00.388 --> 01:52:04.154
...and now the Iraqi people
can do what they wanna do...

01:52:04.325 --> 01:52:06.384
...and really be free?"

01:52:06.561 --> 01:52:09.428
Will they ever be free?
No, they'll not be free.

01:52:09.597 --> 01:52:12.566
And where are the weapons
of mass destruction?

01:52:12.734 --> 01:52:15.669
It was a... We were duped.
We were really duped.

01:52:15.837 --> 01:52:17.304
And these poor people...

01:52:17.472 --> 01:52:20.703
...the young men and women
who are being killed there.

01:52:20.875 --> 01:52:22.604
- It's unnecessary.
- That's a disgrace.

01:52:22.777 --> 01:52:25.041
- That's it. No more.
- That's a disgrace.

01:52:25.213 --> 01:52:28.842
They died in a just cause,
for defending freedom...

01:52:29.017 --> 01:52:32.145
...and they will not
have died in vain.

01:52:43.364 --> 01:52:46.697
Lila had called to tell me
she was coming down from Flint...

01:52:46.868 --> 01:52:50.702
...to Washington, D. C.
to attend a jobs conference.

01:52:51.105 --> 01:52:53.471
On her break, she said
she was going to go...

01:52:53.641 --> 01:52:56.667
...and pay a visit
to the White House.

01:53:03.685 --> 01:53:06.916
Bush killed children. Iraqi children.

01:53:07.088 --> 01:53:10.956
- My son, killed.
- Killed my people in Spain, yesterday.

01:53:11.125 --> 01:53:14.788
- Lies kill people. Your children too.
- Yes, my son.

01:53:14.962 --> 01:53:17.658
They have no business to do
in Iraq now. They're killing...

01:53:17.832 --> 01:53:19.424
...all these young Americans.
- Yes.

01:53:19.600 --> 01:53:23.263
For what? For oil.
Bush is a terrorist.

01:53:23.438 --> 01:53:25.804
- No, he isn't. This is all staged.
- Yes, he is.

01:53:25.973 --> 01:53:28.168
- This is all staged.
- My son.

01:53:28.343 --> 01:53:32.211
- Where was he killed?
- You tell me my son is not a stage.

01:53:32.380 --> 01:53:34.712
- Where was he killed?
- He was killed in Karbala.

01:53:36.384 --> 01:53:40.616
April 2nd. It's not a stage.
My son is dead.

01:53:40.788 --> 01:53:43.382
There are a lot of other people too.

01:53:47.362 --> 01:53:49.387
Blame al Qaeda.

01:53:53.134 --> 01:53:55.068
What did that woman yell at you?

01:53:55.236 --> 01:53:58.467
That I'm supposed
to blame the al Qaeda.

01:53:58.639 --> 01:54:03.201
The al Qaeda didn't make a decision
to send my son to Iraq.

01:54:04.245 --> 01:54:07.772
Ignorance that we deal with,
with everyday people.

01:54:07.949 --> 01:54:10.247
Because they don't know.
People think they know...

01:54:10.418 --> 01:54:14.445
...but you don't know.
I thought I knew, but I didn't know.

01:54:19.527 --> 01:54:22.155
I need my son.

01:54:39.814 --> 01:54:42.339
God, it's tougher than I thought
it was gonna be...

01:54:42.517 --> 01:54:44.382
...to be here.

01:54:45.219 --> 01:54:46.982
But it's freeing also...

01:54:47.155 --> 01:54:49.020
...because I finally have a place...

01:54:49.190 --> 01:54:52.717
...to put all my pain
and all my anger...

01:54:52.894 --> 01:54:54.987
...and to release it.

01:55:00.468 --> 01:55:04.529
I guess I was tired of seeing people
like Lila Lipscomb suffer.

01:55:04.705 --> 01:55:09.165
Especially when, out of
the 535 members of Congress...

01:55:09.343 --> 01:55:12.801
...only one had an enlisted son
in Iraq.

01:55:15.950 --> 01:55:18.851
I asked Corporal Henderson of
the United States Marine Corps...

01:55:19.020 --> 01:55:20.885
...to join me on Capitol Hill...

01:55:21.055 --> 01:55:24.252
...to see how many members
of Congress we could convince...

01:55:24.425 --> 01:55:27.394
...to enlist their children
to go to Iraq.

01:55:27.562 --> 01:55:29.052
Congressman, I'm Michael Moore.

01:55:29.230 --> 01:55:31.494
- Hey, Michael. How are you doing?
- Good.

01:55:31.666 --> 01:55:34.430
- John Tanner, from Tennessee.
- Very nice to meet you.

01:55:34.602 --> 01:55:37.002
- What y'all doing?
- I'm here with Corporal Henderson.

01:55:37.171 --> 01:55:40.629
- United States Marine Corps.
- Corporal, I was in the Navy.

01:55:40.808 --> 01:55:43.299
- 1968 to '72.
- Okay.

01:55:43.478 --> 01:55:45.070
We had Marines guarding the base.

01:55:45.246 --> 01:55:46.508
- You have kids?
- Yeah.

01:55:46.681 --> 01:55:48.842
Is there any way we can
get them to enlist...

01:55:49.016 --> 01:55:51.416
...and go over there
and help out with the effort?

01:55:51.586 --> 01:55:54.714
- I've got all the brochures.
- One of them has got two children.

01:55:56.390 --> 01:55:59.325
See, there's not many congressmen
that have kids over there.

01:55:59.494 --> 01:56:01.724
In fact, only one. You know.

01:56:01.896 --> 01:56:04.228
So we just thought maybe they...

01:56:04.398 --> 01:56:06.832
- You guys should send your kids first.
- That's right.

01:56:07.001 --> 01:56:09.299
- What do you think about that?
- I don't disagree.

01:56:09.470 --> 01:56:12.064
You don't? Oh, good.
Well, take some brochures.

01:56:12.240 --> 01:56:14.265
- At least take a Marine brochure.
- Thank you.

01:56:14.442 --> 01:56:16.069
- Pass it around.
- Yeah, well...

01:56:16.244 --> 01:56:19.907
Encourage the fellow members
if they're for the war to get behind it.

01:56:20.081 --> 01:56:21.514
- Send their own.
- Thank you.

01:56:21.682 --> 01:56:23.980
Thank you, sir.
Thank you very much.

01:56:25.186 --> 01:56:27.677
Congressman? Michael Moore.

01:56:27.855 --> 01:56:29.288
- How you doing today?
- Good.

01:56:29.457 --> 01:56:33.188
I'm trying to get members of Congress
to get their kids to enlist in the Army...

01:56:33.361 --> 01:56:35.556
...and go over to Iraq.

01:56:36.397 --> 01:56:37.796
Congressman.

01:56:37.965 --> 01:56:39.398
Congressman.

01:56:39.567 --> 01:56:41.797
Congressman Castle?
Congressman Castle?

01:56:41.969 --> 01:56:44.199
Congressman. Congressman.

01:56:44.372 --> 01:56:46.533
Congressman Doolittle,
Michael Moore.

01:56:46.707 --> 01:56:48.402
I was wondering if...

01:56:51.546 --> 01:56:53.275
Is there any way to...?

01:56:55.917 --> 01:56:58.044
Of course, not a single member
of Congress...

01:56:58.219 --> 01:57:01.586
...wanted to sacrifice their child
for the war in Iraq.

01:57:02.189 --> 01:57:04.054
And who could blame them?

01:57:04.225 --> 01:57:06.591
Who would wanna give up
their child?

01:57:06.761 --> 01:57:08.661
Would you?

01:57:08.829 --> 01:57:10.592
Would he?

01:57:12.433 --> 01:57:14.560
I've always been amazed
that the very people...

01:57:14.735 --> 01:57:16.896
...forced to live in the worst
parts of town...

01:57:17.438 --> 01:57:20.703
...go to the worst schools
and who have it the hardest...

01:57:20.875 --> 01:57:25.812
...are always the first to step up
to defend that very system.

01:57:25.980 --> 01:57:29.609
They serve so that
we don't have to.

01:57:29.784 --> 01:57:34.687
They offer to give up their lives
so that we can be free.

01:57:34.855 --> 01:57:38.848
It is remarkable, their gift to us.

01:57:39.026 --> 01:57:41.859
And all they ask for in return...

01:57:42.029 --> 01:57:44.793
...is that we never send them
into harm's way...

01:57:45.333 --> 01:57:48.734
...unless it's absolutely necessary.

01:57:50.204 --> 01:57:53.605
Will they ever trust us again?

01:57:53.774 --> 01:57:55.969
He had used weapons.

01:57:56.143 --> 01:57:57.371
We know where they are.

01:57:59.313 --> 01:58:01.838
Around Tikrit, Baghdad
and east, west, south and north.

01:58:02.016 --> 01:58:06.316
There is a tie between Iraq
and what happened on 9l11.

01:58:06.487 --> 01:58:08.512
The struggle can only end...

01:58:08.689 --> 01:58:11.556
...with their complete
and permanent destruction.

01:58:11.726 --> 01:58:15.492
We wage a war to save
civilization itself.

01:58:16.831 --> 01:58:18.890
We did not seek it.

01:58:19.634 --> 01:58:23.365
But we will fight it,
and we will prevail.

01:58:23.537 --> 01:58:25.562
George Orwell once wrote...

01:58:25.740 --> 01:58:30.507
...that, "It's not a matter of whether
the war is not real or if it is.

01:58:30.678 --> 01:58:32.976
Victory is not possible.

01:58:34.048 --> 01:58:39.509
The war is not meant to be won.
It is meant to be continuous.

01:58:39.687 --> 01:58:42.247
A hierarchical society
is only possible...

01:58:42.423 --> 01:58:45.290
...on the basis of poverty
and ignorance.

01:58:46.093 --> 01:58:48.561
This new version is the past...

01:58:48.729 --> 01:58:51.220
...and no different past
can ever have existed.

01:58:53.167 --> 01:58:55.761
In principle, the war effort
is always planned...

01:58:55.936 --> 01:58:59.167
...to keep society
on the brink of starvation.

01:58:59.340 --> 01:59:03.640
The war is waged by the ruling group
against its own subjects.

01:59:03.811 --> 01:59:08.942
And its object is not the victory
over either Eurasia or East Asia...

01:59:09.116 --> 01:59:13.348
...but to keep the very
structure of society intact."

01:59:13.521 --> 01:59:15.455
There's an old saying
in Tennessee.

01:59:15.623 --> 01:59:17.614
I know it's in Texas,
probably in Tennessee.

01:59:17.792 --> 01:59:19.419
Fool me once...

01:59:20.161 --> 01:59:21.958
...shame on...

01:59:22.963 --> 01:59:24.897
Shame on you.

01:59:27.234 --> 01:59:29.225
You fool me,
we can't get fooled again.

01:59:29.403 --> 01:59:31.598
For once, we agreed.

